1
00:00:01,590 --> 00:00:10,000
<b>Hotel Del Luna Blu-ray Disc 1</b>
Subtitle re-timing by Jharel

2
00:03:00,314 --> 00:03:01,734
You were lucky.

3
00:03:02,358 --> 00:03:04,488
This is the only place
you can get a drink.

4
00:03:05,236 --> 00:03:06,566
Are you from Muzu?

5
00:03:07,405 --> 00:03:10,365
You don't exactly look like a Georan.

6
00:03:10,908 --> 00:03:12,538
Are you from Malgal?

7
00:03:13,494 --> 00:03:17,464
My goodness, I see you have a sword.
Are you a warrior?

8
00:03:21,210 --> 00:03:22,920
The wine tastes horrible,

9
00:03:23,003 --> 00:03:24,763
and you're very chatty.

10
00:03:37,143 --> 00:03:38,603
Did someone die?

11
00:03:40,021 --> 00:03:42,861
Or did you kill someone?

12
00:03:45,901 --> 00:03:50,241
There are only two types of people
who pass by this place

13
00:03:50,322 --> 00:03:51,822
even in this kind of weather.

14
00:03:52,158 --> 00:03:54,038
It's either a person who killed someone

15
00:03:54,368 --> 00:03:56,078
or a person who's on their way to die.

16
00:03:56,162 --> 00:03:59,422
Even with that useless
and big mouth of yours,

17
00:04:01,250 --> 00:04:03,290
you've managed to live quite a long life.

18
00:04:03,627 --> 00:04:05,417
Should I slice off your tongue,

19
00:04:05,504 --> 00:04:07,384
so you can safely live longer?

20
00:04:08,090 --> 00:04:11,430
This old tongue of mine
might not be able to taste good wine,

21
00:04:11,510 --> 00:04:13,760
but it knows how to say things
that can be of help.

22
00:04:14,597 --> 00:04:18,057
It seems like you've been wandering
for a very long time.

23
00:04:18,934 --> 00:04:20,814
Where are you trying to go?

24
00:04:23,981 --> 00:04:25,441
I'm looking for a guest house.

25
00:04:25,900 --> 00:04:27,320
I heard there's a guest house

26
00:04:28,110 --> 00:04:31,200
somewhere in this wilderness
that consoles the souls of the dead.

27
00:04:32,364 --> 00:04:34,914
You must be looking
for the Guest House of the Moon.

28
00:04:37,620 --> 00:04:38,580
Do you know that place?

29
00:04:38,662 --> 00:04:40,712
I heard it's a guest house for the dead

30
00:04:40,790 --> 00:04:42,460
who still wander in this life.

31
00:04:42,792 --> 00:04:44,042
Where is that place?

32
00:04:44,543 --> 00:04:45,543
Where do I need to go?

33
00:04:45,628 --> 00:04:49,048
You can't go there.
Only the dead are able to go there.

34
00:04:49,465 --> 00:04:52,375
Just like them over there.

35
00:04:58,140 --> 00:05:03,100
How many souls
have you brought in this coffin?

36
00:05:10,236 --> 00:05:12,066
They're people who ended up
dying because of me.

37
00:05:12,321 --> 00:05:16,411
And who else did you kill
for those who ended up dying?

38
00:05:20,955 --> 00:05:23,285
Shut your mouth.
Just tell me how to get there.

39
00:05:25,668 --> 00:05:27,288
"Full moon"?

40
00:05:27,545 --> 00:05:29,915
It's a moon
that's filled with so many grudges.

41
00:05:30,214 --> 00:05:31,224
Tell me.

42
00:05:31,465 --> 00:05:33,045
I'm trying to take responsibility

43
00:05:34,385 --> 00:05:35,925
for those whom I've killed.

44
00:05:36,011 --> 00:05:38,221
You can't even handle yourself,

45
00:05:38,305 --> 00:05:40,015
and you're trying to take responsibility

46
00:05:40,099 --> 00:05:41,559
for other people's lives?

47
00:05:41,642 --> 00:05:43,602
I told you I'll slice off your tongue

48
00:05:44,854 --> 00:05:46,614
if you ever run your mouth.

49
00:05:47,231 --> 00:05:48,651
Just tell me how to get there.

50
00:05:49,024 --> 00:05:51,114
If that place can only be found
by the dead,

51
00:05:53,112 --> 00:05:54,862
I'm even willing to kill myself.

52
00:05:55,364 --> 00:05:56,874
What a poor soul.

53
00:05:57,491 --> 00:06:00,331
You think you can compensate
for everything by sacrificing your life.

54
00:06:00,411 --> 00:06:02,201
But that's such a futile hope.

55
00:06:02,705 --> 00:06:04,365
My life is the only thing left

56
00:06:05,249 --> 00:06:06,959
that I can give.

57
00:06:07,167 --> 00:06:11,007
FULL MOON

58
00:06:11,505 --> 00:06:13,045
The Guest House of the Moon...

59
00:06:14,967 --> 00:06:17,427
is where the souls of the dead
gather together.

60
00:06:18,637 --> 00:06:22,847
The dead souls that wander about
all end up there of their own free will.

61
00:07:20,199 --> 00:07:24,079
They are also people
you've already killed.

62
00:08:50,289 --> 00:08:51,709
Was this the place?

63
00:08:52,666 --> 00:08:54,416
Did I kill everyone?

64
00:08:55,127 --> 00:08:56,877
Did I become an evil ghost?

65
00:08:58,464 --> 00:09:01,344
And come to the Guest House of the Moon
on my own?

66
00:09:03,761 --> 00:09:06,221
<i>Arrogant and foolish.</i>

67
00:09:06,513 --> 00:09:10,143
<i>You are a pitiful human
who has fallen into self-pity.</i>

68
00:09:11,268 --> 00:09:15,108
<i>You have found the place to pay
for your sins of your own will,</i>

69
00:09:15,230 --> 00:09:17,070
<i>so now pay for your sins.</i>

70
00:09:39,004 --> 00:09:40,764
FULL MOON

71
00:11:08,886 --> 00:11:11,596
GUEST HOUSE

72
00:11:39,958 --> 00:11:44,168
The Guest House of the Moon
which will be the shelter for the dead

73
00:11:44,463 --> 00:11:46,593
has found a new owner.

74
00:11:54,598 --> 00:11:58,058
Why don't you all come with me

75
00:11:58,143 --> 00:12:00,103
to a comfortable place?

76
00:13:06,420 --> 00:13:09,670
YEAR 1998

77
00:13:19,224 --> 00:13:20,234
Son.

78
00:13:21,351 --> 00:13:24,521
It's your birthday today,
but I can't even buy you <i>jajangmyeon</i>.

79
00:13:24,938 --> 00:13:27,318
It's all right. I'm not hungry.

80
00:13:44,249 --> 00:13:46,039
-Mister.
-Hey, son.

81
00:13:46,126 --> 00:13:48,206
-You dropped your money.
-Thank you.

82
00:13:49,755 --> 00:13:52,875
Oh, dear. You're a good boy.

83
00:13:52,966 --> 00:13:55,426
You have a handsome forehead
and twinkling eyes.

84
00:13:55,510 --> 00:13:57,390
You have a very auspicious face.

85
00:13:57,471 --> 00:13:58,851
It's your birthday today?

86
00:13:58,930 --> 00:14:00,640
Tell me the year and hour
that you were born.

87
00:14:00,724 --> 00:14:03,064
Hey, lady. We're not buying flowers.
Just go your way.

88
00:14:03,518 --> 00:14:06,398
Oh, dear. Your early years were so unlucky

89
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:08,730
that you were born to a father like him.

90
00:14:08,982 --> 00:14:11,152
But it's not an ill-fated relationship.

91
00:14:11,234 --> 00:14:15,284
Having a hard life early on means
getting rid of your bad luck in advance

92
00:14:15,364 --> 00:14:16,954
for your future good fortune.

93
00:14:17,032 --> 00:14:18,202
What? "Bad luck"?

94
00:14:18,533 --> 00:14:20,743
How can you talk such rubbish
just to sell flowers to a kid?

95
00:14:21,036 --> 00:14:21,866
Son, just wait.

96
00:14:21,953 --> 00:14:24,123
I'll make lots of money
and buy you your birthday present.

97
00:14:24,331 --> 00:14:25,791
-Present?
-Flowers!

98
00:14:25,874 --> 00:14:28,544
Flowers are the best present
for birthdays.

99
00:14:28,627 --> 00:14:30,337
I'm not buying your flowers!

100
00:14:30,545 --> 00:14:32,045
Flowers are good too.

101
00:14:32,631 --> 00:14:35,511
You can just pluck them for me,
instead of buying them.

102
00:14:35,592 --> 00:14:38,142
So, don't do dangerous things
just to make money.

103
00:14:38,220 --> 00:14:39,550
My goodness.

104
00:14:39,638 --> 00:14:41,718
You're too young
to worry about things like that.

105
00:14:53,193 --> 00:14:54,533
Poke around the place.

106
00:14:54,611 --> 00:14:55,861
Is there anything?

107
00:14:56,613 --> 00:14:59,663
-Over there.
-Check there.

108
00:15:22,597 --> 00:15:23,467
911 EMERGENCY SERVICE

109
00:16:57,442 --> 00:17:00,492
Ms. Jang, are you up?

110
00:17:01,446 --> 00:17:04,736
It's the full moon, so I think
we will have many guests today.

111
00:17:04,825 --> 00:17:07,985
When the moon is bright,
they can see this place from far away.

112
00:17:09,079 --> 00:17:12,039
So they will crawl in here
from all over the place.

113
00:17:12,207 --> 00:17:15,707
All right, then.
I will light up the hotel sign.

114
00:17:16,670 --> 00:17:17,710
Open the hotel for business.

115
00:17:18,588 --> 00:17:20,838
I get into a bad mood
when I see the full moon.

116
00:17:21,132 --> 00:17:22,802
And today, it's particularly worse.

117
00:17:23,301 --> 00:17:25,261
Don't let in anyone
whose death was too gruesome.

118
00:17:25,345 --> 00:17:27,505
We shouldn't pick guests--

119
00:17:27,597 --> 00:17:28,717
Don't accept them.

120
00:17:28,807 --> 00:17:31,017
They won't be in a rush
since they're already dead.

121
00:17:31,101 --> 00:17:35,151
I will take special care,
so they won't get in your way.

122
00:17:42,153 --> 00:17:43,663
That darn moon.

123
00:17:46,950 --> 00:17:48,700
I'm so sick of it.

124
00:19:06,196 --> 00:19:07,276
Stop right there!

125
00:19:07,489 --> 00:19:08,619
Stop!

126
00:19:31,471 --> 00:19:32,471
My gosh.

127
00:19:34,599 --> 00:19:36,349
Gosh, I almost died.

128
00:20:03,169 --> 00:20:04,299
What's that?

129
00:20:18,018 --> 00:20:20,688
I wonder if I'll have to pay
just for going inside.

130
00:20:47,380 --> 00:20:48,510
Are you here alone?

131
00:20:51,134 --> 00:20:53,724
Do you remember how long it's been
since you died?

132
00:20:54,554 --> 00:20:55,684
It's been about ten days.

133
00:21:05,607 --> 00:21:07,567
I guess that's the elevator.

134
00:21:34,344 --> 00:21:36,554
My gosh, this place is huge.

135
00:21:44,938 --> 00:21:47,018
I wonder if I'll have to pay
just for sitting here.

136
00:21:51,236 --> 00:21:52,356
Are you okay?

137
00:21:52,904 --> 00:21:53,994
You don't look so well.

138
00:21:54,614 --> 00:21:56,284
Where did you get so wet?

139
00:21:57,992 --> 00:21:59,202
The Han River.

140
00:21:59,285 --> 00:22:00,365
The Han River?

141
00:22:03,873 --> 00:22:06,043
Did she play in the water
in the middle of the night?

142
00:22:07,961 --> 00:22:08,921
Is this place expensive?

143
00:22:09,045 --> 00:22:11,505
Do you think they'll make me pay
just for sitting in the lobby?

144
00:22:11,589 --> 00:22:14,379
I don't know. This is my first time here.

145
00:22:18,763 --> 00:22:19,763
What happened...

146
00:22:20,932 --> 00:22:22,182
to you?

147
00:22:22,267 --> 00:22:24,517
I fell down the stairs.

148
00:22:50,879 --> 00:22:53,209
It's been a while since we last had
a ghost soaked in water.

149
00:22:53,506 --> 00:22:55,126
-A ghost soaked in water?
-Yes.

150
00:22:55,216 --> 00:22:57,336
By any chance,
does that ghost look horrible?

151
00:22:57,719 --> 00:22:59,389
Well, a little...

152
00:22:59,596 --> 00:23:01,556
Ms. Jang isn't feeling very well today.

153
00:23:01,639 --> 00:23:04,729
Let's take the guest to her room quickly
so that Ms. Jang doesn't see her.

154
00:23:04,851 --> 00:23:05,851
Okay, sir.

155
00:23:15,403 --> 00:23:17,033
What's wrong, sir?

156
00:23:17,113 --> 00:23:18,783
The guest that just walked by...

157
00:23:19,490 --> 00:23:22,370
He doesn't belong here.
He came to the wrong place.

158
00:23:23,328 --> 00:23:24,908
Does that mean

159
00:23:25,705 --> 00:23:26,955
he isn't dead?

160
00:23:27,707 --> 00:23:28,627
Is he alive?

161
00:23:28,708 --> 00:23:31,248
If Ms. Jang sees him, he'll die.

162
00:23:32,086 --> 00:23:34,046
We need to get him out of here
as soon as possible.

163
00:23:39,010 --> 00:23:41,100
I need to hide here
for at least a couple of hours.

164
00:23:41,262 --> 00:23:42,972
Should I hide in the bathroom?

165
00:23:43,306 --> 00:23:45,216
Yes, good idea.
Let's hide in the bathroom.

166
00:23:53,107 --> 00:23:54,187
Is this gold?

167
00:23:57,612 --> 00:23:59,822
My gosh, this looks really expensive.

168
00:24:03,159 --> 00:24:05,949
No. This isn't important right now.

169
00:24:09,290 --> 00:24:10,880
I hope I see you again.

170
00:25:00,049 --> 00:25:01,509
Why is there a sea here?

171
00:25:03,094 --> 00:25:05,894
Sir, would you like to swim in the water?

172
00:25:06,681 --> 00:25:08,811
We'll lend you a swimsuit.

173
00:25:09,142 --> 00:25:10,482
What's your room number?

174
00:25:10,810 --> 00:25:13,350
No, I'm okay.

175
00:25:27,702 --> 00:25:28,582
Welcome.

176
00:25:53,978 --> 00:25:55,648
I didn't know this building was this tall.

177
00:25:59,859 --> 00:26:01,029
How weird.

178
00:26:03,154 --> 00:26:04,204
That's scary.

179
00:26:06,282 --> 00:26:08,202
A living person is here?

180
00:26:08,826 --> 00:26:10,366
It seems like he's roaming around

181
00:26:10,453 --> 00:26:12,833
without even knowing
what this place really is.

182
00:26:12,914 --> 00:26:15,374
If he doesn't leave soon, he'll die.

183
00:26:15,458 --> 00:26:17,288
The worst he'll have to face is death,

184
00:26:17,376 --> 00:26:19,666
but we'll get scolded so much
if Ms. Jang finds out.

185
00:26:19,754 --> 00:26:21,924
She'll make sure we don't forget
about this for 50 years.

186
00:26:22,006 --> 00:26:23,586
You know what she always says.

187
00:26:26,594 --> 00:26:28,304
Is this the best you can do?

188
00:26:30,306 --> 00:26:32,226
You guys must think of me as a joke.

189
00:26:33,976 --> 00:26:35,976
If you make this kind of mistake
one more time,

190
00:26:36,104 --> 00:26:39,824
I'll put all of you on a bus
that's headed to the afterlife.

191
00:26:40,233 --> 00:26:41,283
Do you understand?

192
00:26:45,738 --> 00:26:46,818
My gosh, no way.

193
00:26:47,573 --> 00:26:50,333
I feel like it's my fault.
What should I do?

194
00:26:50,451 --> 00:26:52,161
Yes, it's all your fault.

195
00:26:52,245 --> 00:26:54,155
-This one's on you.
-What?

196
00:26:54,247 --> 00:26:55,667
I can't take responsibility for this.

197
00:26:55,748 --> 00:26:57,288
I still have stuff to do in this life.

198
00:26:57,375 --> 00:26:59,875
I can't get on the bus
headed to the afterlife.

199
00:27:00,503 --> 00:27:01,503
I'm doomed.

200
00:27:01,587 --> 00:27:04,717
Why did that dumb human
have to come here? Darn it.

201
00:27:04,799 --> 00:27:06,629
I'm sure Ms. Jang will notice
sooner or later

202
00:27:06,717 --> 00:27:09,297
that a living human soul is roaming
around the hotel.

203
00:27:09,929 --> 00:27:13,929
If Ms. Jang finds him,
he'll never be able to leave this place.

204
00:27:14,225 --> 00:27:15,845
He'll end up dying.

205
00:27:26,737 --> 00:27:28,567
A thief must be here.

206
00:27:30,867 --> 00:27:32,617
How dare anyone steal from my hotel?

207
00:28:01,522 --> 00:28:03,022
What's this place?

208
00:28:12,992 --> 00:28:13,832
Flowers?

209
00:28:16,662 --> 00:28:18,162
Flowers are good too.

210
00:28:18,247 --> 00:28:21,417
You can just pluck them for me,
instead of buying them.

211
00:28:21,500 --> 00:28:22,790
This is good.

212
00:28:23,502 --> 00:28:25,132
I'll take them to Chan-sung.

213
00:28:25,713 --> 00:28:27,923
This looks like a dead tree.

214
00:28:28,132 --> 00:28:30,092
But the flowers are really pretty.

215
00:29:02,458 --> 00:29:03,538
What is this?

216
00:29:04,335 --> 00:29:06,125
I see you're feeling pain.

217
00:29:07,129 --> 00:29:09,009
Does that mean you're alive?

218
00:29:10,174 --> 00:29:11,224
Who are you?

219
00:29:11,300 --> 00:29:12,760
What are you doing? Move your foot.

220
00:29:13,177 --> 00:29:14,717
You stole from me.

221
00:29:14,804 --> 00:29:16,684
I didn't do anything.

222
00:29:16,764 --> 00:29:18,644
I didn't steal anything here.

223
00:29:19,016 --> 00:29:21,226
Really? Then, what is this?

224
00:29:28,359 --> 00:29:29,779
That is...

225
00:29:30,653 --> 00:29:32,033
You tried to steal it.

226
00:29:32,238 --> 00:29:33,278
That is...

227
00:29:34,156 --> 00:29:35,986
Do you want to get bitten to death by him?

228
00:29:40,871 --> 00:29:41,871
I'm sorry.

229
00:29:41,956 --> 00:29:43,036
Please forgive me.

230
00:29:43,291 --> 00:29:44,831
I deserve to die for my sins.

231
00:29:44,917 --> 00:29:45,787
Then, die.

232
00:29:46,377 --> 00:29:48,957
No, I can't die now.

233
00:29:49,046 --> 00:29:51,256
All humans have to die at the end.

234
00:29:51,799 --> 00:29:53,839
Instead of going back and forth,

235
00:29:54,176 --> 00:29:55,386
since you're already here,

236
00:29:55,970 --> 00:29:56,890
die now.

237
00:29:58,848 --> 00:30:00,428
I don't think you realized this.

238
00:30:01,142 --> 00:30:02,852
But you are already dying.

239
00:30:08,190 --> 00:30:10,070
What's happening to me?

240
00:30:10,318 --> 00:30:12,278
What's going on?

241
00:30:16,532 --> 00:30:18,242
Check his pulse and oxygen saturation.

242
00:30:18,618 --> 00:30:20,448
Oxygen saturation is critical.

243
00:30:20,995 --> 00:30:22,535
Get me the defibrillator.

244
00:30:23,414 --> 00:30:25,124
Two hundred joules. Charge. Clear!

245
00:30:26,542 --> 00:30:28,172
<i>I can't die now.</i>

246
00:30:28,836 --> 00:30:29,996
<i>Please spare me.</i>

247
00:30:30,630 --> 00:30:32,210
My son is waiting for me.

248
00:30:32,298 --> 00:30:33,878
I feel sorry for your son.

249
00:30:42,099 --> 00:30:43,019
What is this?

250
00:30:43,100 --> 00:30:44,440
Today is my son's birthday.

251
00:30:44,518 --> 00:30:46,348
He wanted flowers for his present.

252
00:30:46,812 --> 00:30:48,232
So I got them from the tree.

253
00:30:48,397 --> 00:30:50,477
I am really sorry. I mean it.

254
00:30:51,317 --> 00:30:54,567
Flowers never bloom on this tree.

255
00:30:54,654 --> 00:30:56,534
The flowers are from this tree for sure.

256
00:30:56,614 --> 00:30:58,494
I didn't touch anything else.

257
00:31:02,328 --> 00:31:04,288
You made flowers for this human

258
00:31:04,372 --> 00:31:05,792
and gave away your branch?

259
00:31:09,377 --> 00:31:10,917
Is it telling me to spare him?

260
00:31:17,051 --> 00:31:18,681
This is your son's birthday present?

261
00:31:18,761 --> 00:31:21,971
Unlike a foolish father like me,
he is a smart and loyal son.

262
00:31:22,765 --> 00:31:25,725
If you forgive me this once,
I will never steal anything again.

263
00:31:25,810 --> 00:31:27,690
I will raise my son as best as I can.

264
00:31:30,147 --> 00:31:30,977
Okay.

265
00:31:31,357 --> 00:31:32,227
Good.

266
00:31:34,568 --> 00:31:35,858
I will spare you.

267
00:31:36,612 --> 00:31:38,242
Thank you very much.

268
00:31:38,864 --> 00:31:41,374
You go back and raise your son well.

269
00:31:42,410 --> 00:31:44,250
Raise him well...

270
00:31:45,830 --> 00:31:46,960
and give him to me.

271
00:31:47,540 --> 00:31:48,370
What?

272
00:31:48,457 --> 00:31:50,997
Since I saved the father,
the son must repay me.

273
00:31:51,293 --> 00:31:52,673
You said he was still young, yes?

274
00:31:52,795 --> 00:31:55,375
If a human is to be of any use,

275
00:31:55,464 --> 00:31:58,804
you need to feed and raise him
for at least 20 years.

276
00:31:59,176 --> 00:32:02,676
Promise me to give me your son then.

277
00:32:03,013 --> 00:32:04,353
You want my son?

278
00:32:04,432 --> 00:32:06,392
If you don't like it, you die tonight.

279
00:32:09,937 --> 00:32:12,477
What? No. Wait.

280
00:32:15,985 --> 00:32:17,445
Hurry up and make up your mind.

281
00:32:17,778 --> 00:32:21,658
If you don't decide in a few minutes,
you'll die.

282
00:32:22,992 --> 00:32:24,242
How can I...

283
00:32:25,244 --> 00:32:28,164
If I die, Chan-sung will be all alone.

284
00:32:28,748 --> 00:32:29,868
What will you do?

285
00:32:30,416 --> 00:32:33,246
Will you give me your son, or...

286
00:32:33,919 --> 00:32:34,999
die now?

287
00:32:36,881 --> 00:32:38,221
I'll give you my son.

288
00:32:38,966 --> 00:32:40,176
Please spare me.

289
00:32:42,511 --> 00:32:43,431
Okay.

290
00:32:43,804 --> 00:32:44,684
Good.

291
00:32:49,310 --> 00:32:50,730
Twenty years later,

292
00:32:51,437 --> 00:32:53,017
I will go to get your son.

293
00:32:57,902 --> 00:32:58,902
Go.

294
00:33:03,824 --> 00:33:04,914
Dad.

295
00:33:08,746 --> 00:33:10,156
Chan-sung.

296
00:33:12,291 --> 00:33:14,001
My dad is not dead.

297
00:33:14,668 --> 00:33:15,668
What?

298
00:33:19,048 --> 00:33:21,178
His reflex has come back,
and his vitals are okay.

299
00:33:21,258 --> 00:33:22,088
Contact the Orthopedics

300
00:33:22,176 --> 00:33:23,546
-and prepare for an operation.
-I will.

301
00:33:23,636 --> 00:33:24,846
Wait here, okay?

302
00:33:26,263 --> 00:33:27,353
Dad.

303
00:33:30,392 --> 00:33:31,442
Chan-sung.

304
00:33:34,730 --> 00:33:35,770
Come here.

305
00:33:41,695 --> 00:33:42,695
Dad.

306
00:33:57,211 --> 00:33:59,051
He left his son's birthday present.

307
00:34:35,082 --> 00:34:36,792
FUNERAL HALL

308
00:34:37,877 --> 00:34:38,917
That woman...

309
00:34:39,753 --> 00:34:40,753
<i>I don't know.</i>

310
00:34:41,213 --> 00:34:42,633
This is my first time here.

311
00:34:45,092 --> 00:34:47,642
Dad, do you know that policewoman?

312
00:34:51,390 --> 00:34:54,730
I don't know her,
but I think I saw her somewhere.

313
00:34:55,853 --> 00:34:57,943
Is it possible that wasn't a dream?

314
00:35:07,031 --> 00:35:08,371
I'm a policewoman.

315
00:35:08,782 --> 00:35:10,872
I was an undercover cop,
and my identity was exposed.

316
00:35:10,993 --> 00:35:11,913
And I was killed.

317
00:35:11,994 --> 00:35:13,544
Such a pity.

318
00:35:13,954 --> 00:35:16,624
You died doing righteous work.
So when you leave for the afterlife,

319
00:35:16,707 --> 00:35:18,747
you will be provided
with a first-class limousine.

320
00:35:19,460 --> 00:35:21,710
Rest for a few days here,
then take the limousine.

321
00:35:21,962 --> 00:35:23,462
I can't leave like this.

322
00:35:24,548 --> 00:35:26,588
Most of my guests say the same thing.

323
00:35:27,092 --> 00:35:28,342
What would you like me to do?

324
00:35:28,427 --> 00:35:29,757
Do you want revenge?

325
00:35:29,929 --> 00:35:31,599
For your reference,
even if you want revenge,

326
00:35:31,680 --> 00:35:33,310
we can't take the life of a human.

327
00:35:33,390 --> 00:35:36,190
We can torment him a little.
But that will become a sin

328
00:35:36,268 --> 00:35:38,478
and affect your next life negatively.

329
00:35:39,480 --> 00:35:42,320
You're entitled to be reborn
as something much better.

330
00:35:42,524 --> 00:35:46,114
But you might be reborn as a dog or a pig
if you take that revenge.

331
00:35:46,737 --> 00:35:47,907
Please think carefully.

332
00:35:48,739 --> 00:35:50,159
I don't want revenge.

333
00:35:51,492 --> 00:35:55,122
The man I was chasing
can't be caught by human laws.

334
00:35:56,538 --> 00:35:57,618
So I want to catch him.

335
00:35:59,208 --> 00:36:00,418
You are

336
00:36:00,960 --> 00:36:02,800
such a responsible person.

337
00:36:03,087 --> 00:36:04,797
You have to pay with the worldly money.

338
00:36:04,880 --> 00:36:06,920
for services related
to the world of the living.

339
00:36:07,007 --> 00:36:07,967
Do you have

340
00:36:08,926 --> 00:36:10,756
some money hidden in this world?

341
00:36:18,894 --> 00:36:19,904
Okay.

342
00:36:20,688 --> 00:36:22,188
What can we do for you?

343
00:36:45,254 --> 00:36:48,174
<i>Park Gyu-ho, Mayor of Beomcheon,
is with us here.</i>

344
00:36:52,761 --> 00:36:56,221
Now, we will begin the Businessman Award

345
00:36:56,306 --> 00:36:58,806
for Innovative Growth of Beomcheon City.

346
00:36:59,935 --> 00:37:02,225
The award goes to Mr. Kim Dong-hwan,
CEO of Beomin Corporation.

347
00:37:02,312 --> 00:37:03,152
Congratulations!

348
00:37:04,356 --> 00:37:05,896
-Way to go!
-Way to go!

349
00:37:05,983 --> 00:37:08,613
It will be awarded by Mr. Park Gyu-ho,

350
00:37:08,694 --> 00:37:10,864
-the Mayor of Beomcheon City.
-Kim Dong-hwan!

351
00:37:10,946 --> 00:37:12,776
The CEO has led Beomin Corporation

352
00:37:12,865 --> 00:37:14,155
with exceptional dedication.

353
00:37:14,241 --> 00:37:16,661
He has been an excellent model
as a business manager.

354
00:37:26,962 --> 00:37:29,132
-What is this noise?
-What is this?

355
00:37:29,757 --> 00:37:31,087
-What's going on?
-What is this?

356
00:37:32,342 --> 00:37:33,302
Hey!

357
00:37:40,809 --> 00:37:41,979
Why isn't anyone taking photos?

358
00:37:54,990 --> 00:37:56,030
Who's that?

359
00:38:02,664 --> 00:38:04,834
There's a woman with a gun
in her hand walking in.

360
00:38:05,042 --> 00:38:06,422
Why isn't anyone stopping her?

361
00:38:07,086 --> 00:38:09,836
She has a gun right there!

362
00:38:09,922 --> 00:38:11,262
Hey!

363
00:38:11,673 --> 00:38:13,013
Put your gun down.

364
00:38:53,173 --> 00:38:54,173
Mr. Mayor.

365
00:38:54,383 --> 00:38:56,513
I've been shot.

366
00:38:57,386 --> 00:38:59,176
Shot? What are you talking about?

367
00:38:59,680 --> 00:39:01,890
That woman right there
shot me with her gun.

368
00:39:10,816 --> 00:39:12,396
She really shot me.

369
00:39:19,074 --> 00:39:19,954
Detective Lee?

370
00:39:20,325 --> 00:39:21,445
You died.

371
00:39:23,078 --> 00:39:24,448
Don't come near me!

372
00:39:24,955 --> 00:39:26,495
Get away from me.

373
00:39:32,004 --> 00:39:34,014
That's Detective Lee right there,
isn't it?

374
00:39:34,089 --> 00:39:36,379
What are you all doing? Stop it.

375
00:39:36,466 --> 00:39:37,756
You jerk!

376
00:39:38,635 --> 00:39:39,635
Stop.

377
00:39:39,970 --> 00:39:40,970
Don't come this way!

378
00:39:41,930 --> 00:39:43,890
Stop taking photos.

379
00:39:52,399 --> 00:39:53,529
She's getting away!

380
00:39:54,651 --> 00:39:58,201
Hey! Stop it. Don't come near me.

381
00:40:12,711 --> 00:40:16,381
You put her deep-seated grudge
in the heart of a man she couldn't arrest.

382
00:40:16,715 --> 00:40:19,715
It's like trapping him in a place
that's worse than jail.

383
00:40:19,801 --> 00:40:22,851
She'll be glued to him until she
breaks him, and after she's satisfied,

384
00:40:23,013 --> 00:40:24,563
she'll come back to this hotel.

385
00:40:26,600 --> 00:40:28,640
Have you found what the woman
mentioned earlier?

386
00:40:28,727 --> 00:40:29,597
Yes.

387
00:40:30,896 --> 00:40:33,016
I found this in a locker
at the train station.

388
00:40:35,442 --> 00:40:38,452
They must be smuggled goods she seized
during the undercover operation.

389
00:40:42,449 --> 00:40:46,369
Seems like I can drink as much champagne
as I want for the time being.

390
00:40:46,453 --> 00:40:50,043
We have to pay off the debt that we have.

391
00:40:50,791 --> 00:40:51,921
Did we have this much debt?

392
00:40:54,920 --> 00:40:57,800
Fine, this should be enough.

393
00:40:57,881 --> 00:41:01,091
We also need some to pay off
the future loans.

394
00:41:01,760 --> 00:41:03,010
Are we going to borrow this much?

395
00:41:03,929 --> 00:41:06,519
What kind of hotel management
costs this much money?

396
00:41:06,598 --> 00:41:10,138
All the loans are for your car,
your shopping,

397
00:41:10,644 --> 00:41:12,194
as well as champagne.

398
00:41:13,438 --> 00:41:15,768
It doesn't cost much to run our hotel.

399
00:41:20,195 --> 00:41:23,655
The guy that worked for me before
knew how to work with money,

400
00:41:23,740 --> 00:41:25,740
so I never had to worry
about the finances.

401
00:41:25,826 --> 00:41:28,196
I heard that you were starving
and completely broke

402
00:41:28,287 --> 00:41:31,917
because of another man
that worked for you before that.

403
00:41:33,125 --> 00:41:35,125
It angers me whenever I think of him.

404
00:41:35,919 --> 00:41:39,459
Why don't you invest a little in advance
in whoever will come after me?

405
00:41:39,798 --> 00:41:42,968
I'll pay for 20 years
of child expenses with this.

406
00:41:43,051 --> 00:41:43,971
Hold on.

407
00:41:44,052 --> 00:41:46,352
Does it really cost this much
to raise a kid?

408
00:41:51,768 --> 00:41:52,768
Fine.

409
00:41:53,061 --> 00:41:54,231
Give it all away.

410
00:41:54,855 --> 00:41:56,475
When that kid grows up,

411
00:41:56,940 --> 00:41:59,190
I'm going to have him at my beck and call.

412
00:42:08,410 --> 00:42:11,080
100,000,000 WON TRANSFERRED

413
00:42:11,705 --> 00:42:14,165
I guess it wasn't just a dream.

414
00:42:15,625 --> 00:42:17,875
I guess I really sold you off.

415
00:42:19,588 --> 00:42:21,048
I have to find the hotel.

416
00:42:21,131 --> 00:42:23,931
I have to give this money back
and call off the deal.

417
00:42:25,844 --> 00:42:26,934
Be careful, Dad.

418
00:42:42,903 --> 00:42:44,573
It was somewhere around here.

419
00:42:45,822 --> 00:42:48,872
Stay here. Don't move.

420
00:43:26,571 --> 00:43:29,161
<i>Send him flowers every birthday,</i>

421
00:43:29,658 --> 00:43:31,278
<i>so that he doesn't forget about the deal.</i>

422
00:43:34,371 --> 00:43:36,161
<i>Evening primrose will be perfect.</i>

423
00:44:03,567 --> 00:44:06,357
YEAR 2019

424
00:44:07,070 --> 00:44:10,200
PRESENT

425
00:44:48,153 --> 00:44:49,153
Mr. Koo Chan-sung.

426
00:44:51,364 --> 00:44:52,744
Ms. President is here.

427
00:44:52,949 --> 00:44:53,949
I'll walk you in.

428
00:44:54,242 --> 00:44:55,242
Okay.

429
00:45:00,040 --> 00:45:01,370
RESUME

430
00:45:02,709 --> 00:45:04,379
You won't regret moving

431
00:45:04,461 --> 00:45:07,011
from the Singapore hotel to ours.

432
00:45:07,464 --> 00:45:08,924
I'm looking forward to working with you.

433
00:45:11,635 --> 00:45:14,005
Thank you for trusting me
with such a big role.

434
00:45:16,890 --> 00:45:19,350
You rejected our offer last year,

435
00:45:19,434 --> 00:45:21,564
but you said yes right away
this year. Why?

436
00:45:21,645 --> 00:45:23,185
Because it has been 20 years now.

437
00:45:23,813 --> 00:45:26,323
I made a promise with my father

438
00:45:26,816 --> 00:45:30,026
that I wouldn't come back to Korea
for 20 years.

439
00:45:30,612 --> 00:45:32,362
Last year was the 20th year,

440
00:45:32,447 --> 00:45:34,907
so I could come back this year.

441
00:45:34,991 --> 00:45:36,831
He must have some reasons
to make you promise so.

442
00:45:36,910 --> 00:45:39,750
It's nothing like being in debt
or having committed a crime.

443
00:45:39,829 --> 00:45:42,039
He just wanted me to avoid
anything unfortunate.

444
00:45:42,707 --> 00:45:44,327
It's a kind of superstition.

445
00:45:45,293 --> 00:45:46,843
Old folk do that.

446
00:45:46,920 --> 00:45:49,710
They tell you to avoid things
like getting married when you're 29.

447
00:45:50,340 --> 00:45:52,840
But it never hurts to avoid bad luck.

448
00:45:56,179 --> 00:45:59,179
Do you know, by any chance,
any hotel in Seoul

449
00:45:59,307 --> 00:46:01,307
that's covered with ivy on the outside,

450
00:46:01,768 --> 00:46:05,358
has a rooftop bar located
almost a hundred floors up

451
00:46:06,147 --> 00:46:09,567
and has a pool
that's almost as wide as the sea?

452
00:46:10,151 --> 00:46:11,651
Was there such a hotel 20 years ago?

453
00:46:12,862 --> 00:46:13,782
Sorry?

454
00:46:16,199 --> 00:46:17,199
No, right?

455
00:46:18,994 --> 00:46:21,204
I've sent up all your belongings
to your office.

456
00:46:21,329 --> 00:46:22,159
Thank you.

457
00:46:22,247 --> 00:46:23,537
Did you find a place to stay?

458
00:46:23,623 --> 00:46:25,543
I'll be staying at my friend's house
for now.

459
00:46:25,625 --> 00:46:27,535
I guess that's why
your birthday present came here.

460
00:46:27,794 --> 00:46:29,964
Happy birthday.
It's your birthday today, isn't it?

461
00:46:30,797 --> 00:46:33,167
We've put the present at the front desk.

462
00:46:33,717 --> 00:46:34,717
Wait.

463
00:46:36,052 --> 00:46:37,472
Is the present...

464
00:46:38,054 --> 00:46:39,104
It's flowers.

465
00:46:39,264 --> 00:46:40,814
I can't remember the name...

466
00:46:41,016 --> 00:46:42,266
Evening primrose.

467
00:46:44,185 --> 00:46:45,345
I'm pretty sure.

468
00:46:50,859 --> 00:46:53,149
It's been over 20 years.
Why am I still getting these?

469
00:47:02,120 --> 00:47:03,000
Don't be scared.

470
00:47:03,079 --> 00:47:04,659
You've been getting these all your life.

471
00:47:08,543 --> 00:47:09,543
What is this?

472
00:47:09,753 --> 00:47:11,173
"Hotel del Luna"?

473
00:47:18,053 --> 00:47:18,893
DEAR KOO CHAN-SUNG

474
00:47:18,970 --> 00:47:20,890
BE INFORMED THAT YOU'VE
BEEN HIRED BY HOTEL DEL LUNA

475
00:47:20,972 --> 00:47:21,972
YOUR WORK STARTS TOMORROW

476
00:47:22,307 --> 00:47:24,807
Darn it. This hotel actually exists?

477
00:47:25,685 --> 00:47:26,935
There's even an address.

478
00:47:27,854 --> 00:47:28,864
"Myeong-dong"?

479
00:47:39,032 --> 00:47:40,242
"Myeong-dong."

480
00:47:40,617 --> 00:47:41,867
Should I really go there?

481
00:47:47,123 --> 00:47:48,833
DEAR KOO CHAN-SUNG, HAPPY BIRTHDAY

482
00:48:07,310 --> 00:48:08,810
Excuse me. Let me through.

483
00:48:09,813 --> 00:48:10,813
Excuse me.

484
00:48:11,147 --> 00:48:12,187
Sorry.

485
00:48:40,427 --> 00:48:41,967
DEAR KOO CHAN-SUNG, HAPPY BIRTHDAY

486
00:49:09,581 --> 00:49:10,711
Are you the one?

487
00:49:11,458 --> 00:49:12,578
Are you the one that bought me?

488
00:49:14,711 --> 00:49:16,501
I guess you've been preparing
yourself for this.

489
00:49:17,380 --> 00:49:19,300
I thought you'd ask me who I am first.

490
00:49:19,382 --> 00:49:21,092
I didn't have to ask.

491
00:49:21,885 --> 00:49:23,675
You're just like how my father described.

492
00:49:25,013 --> 00:49:28,063
You're Ms. Jang Man-wol,
the owner of Hotel del Luna, right?

493
00:49:29,100 --> 00:49:32,230
The woman who has been sending me
flowers every birthday.

494
00:49:33,313 --> 00:49:35,693
Did you throw my flowers away every year

495
00:49:35,773 --> 00:49:37,653
like you did today?

496
00:49:37,734 --> 00:49:41,204
Every time I got them, I got scared
that what my father told me might be true.

497
00:49:42,864 --> 00:49:44,374
I was scared that you'd come for me.

498
00:49:46,034 --> 00:49:48,584
Is that why you've been moving
from one country to another?

499
00:49:48,828 --> 00:49:50,458
So that I wouldn't be able to come
and get you?

500
00:49:51,122 --> 00:49:52,462
I've been fleeing,

501
00:49:52,999 --> 00:49:54,579
but I didn't expect you to really come.

502
00:49:55,168 --> 00:49:57,588
I just thought that
everything was over last year.

503
00:49:57,670 --> 00:50:00,050
That's what I intended.
So I came this year instead.

504
00:50:00,298 --> 00:50:02,838
Now that you enjoyed
a nice one-year break,

505
00:50:03,593 --> 00:50:05,053
come start working. Starting tomorrow.

506
00:50:05,386 --> 00:50:07,806
My father told me
that you're a scary person.

507
00:50:08,890 --> 00:50:10,480
Will you kill me if I say no?

508
00:50:15,104 --> 00:50:16,154
You...

509
00:50:17,232 --> 00:50:19,072
aren't scared of me, are you?

510
00:50:21,903 --> 00:50:25,243
I know, I'm too pretty to look scary.

511
00:50:27,784 --> 00:50:28,834
I agree.

512
00:50:29,702 --> 00:50:31,872
So I'll keep thinking
that you're not a scary person

513
00:50:32,038 --> 00:50:33,288
and reject the offer.

514
00:50:36,292 --> 00:50:38,842
It was a bad idea to send you
flowers every birthday.

515
00:50:39,254 --> 00:50:41,424
I should've sent beheaded birds instead.

516
00:50:45,051 --> 00:50:46,141
DEAR KOO CHAN-SUNG

517
00:50:48,054 --> 00:50:49,474
I'll give you something different

518
00:50:50,181 --> 00:50:51,851
for your birthday this year.

519
00:51:20,628 --> 00:51:22,208
You must be someone incredibly powerful

520
00:51:22,297 --> 00:51:24,127
and your hotel must be
really great as well.

521
00:51:24,215 --> 00:51:26,925
How can a weak human being like me
be of any use to you?

522
00:51:28,428 --> 00:51:30,638
Can't you just give me up?

523
00:51:40,148 --> 00:51:41,148
You are...

524
00:51:42,775 --> 00:51:46,315
not going to make me the beheaded bird
as my birthday present, are you?

525
00:52:12,513 --> 00:52:13,643
Don't worry,

526
00:52:14,474 --> 00:52:15,894
"a weak human being."

527
00:52:16,726 --> 00:52:19,146
Your neck is still intact.

528
00:52:23,441 --> 00:52:24,531
What...

529
00:52:26,069 --> 00:52:27,279
have you done to me?

530
00:52:27,737 --> 00:52:28,857
I gave you a present.

531
00:52:31,908 --> 00:52:33,408
Happy birthday.

532
00:52:33,534 --> 00:52:37,334
This year's present is going to be
a very special one.

533
00:52:37,872 --> 00:52:39,542
DEAR KOO CHAN-SUNG, HAPPY BIRTHDAY

534
00:52:59,394 --> 00:53:00,654
Aren't you going to get off?

535
00:53:11,406 --> 00:53:12,736
You want to spend more time with me?

536
00:53:19,122 --> 00:53:22,582
I didn't mean to throw away
the flowers you sent me for my birthday.

537
00:53:23,543 --> 00:53:26,053
They didn't allow me
to bring the flowers at the airport.

538
00:53:57,493 --> 00:53:59,003
What did she do to me?

539
00:54:02,790 --> 00:54:04,830
What is she planning to do with me?

540
00:54:11,632 --> 00:54:12,972
Am I going to become her toy?

541
00:54:15,386 --> 00:54:17,506
<i>Chan-sung, run away.</i>

542
00:54:19,891 --> 00:54:21,231
It's a scary place.

543
00:54:23,102 --> 00:54:26,562
I saw a dead person there.

544
00:54:30,109 --> 00:54:32,529
Chan-sung, run away.

545
00:54:33,654 --> 00:54:35,204
You have to run away

546
00:54:35,281 --> 00:54:37,161
if you ever run into that woman.

547
00:54:38,409 --> 00:54:39,619
<i>Okay, Father.</i>

548
00:54:43,623 --> 00:54:44,833
<i>Run away.</i>

549
00:54:45,082 --> 00:54:46,542
<i>You have to run.</i>

550
00:55:14,070 --> 00:55:17,240
Sorry, I won't be able to start working
from next week.

551
00:55:17,657 --> 00:55:19,987
I'll explain further by email.

552
00:55:48,688 --> 00:55:51,938
<i>By now, he would have received
his birthday present</i>

553
00:55:53,025 --> 00:55:55,025
and opened his eyes to a whole new world.

554
00:55:55,361 --> 00:55:57,111
He probably can't help but panic

555
00:55:57,196 --> 00:56:00,156
when he starts seeing the dead.

556
00:56:00,449 --> 00:56:01,909
He must get used to it.

557
00:56:01,993 --> 00:56:03,743
Since he has to work at this hotel,

558
00:56:03,870 --> 00:56:05,830
he should be able to see the customers.

559
00:56:05,913 --> 00:56:08,123
You said you didn't even warn him.

560
00:56:08,291 --> 00:56:10,001
He might get into a serious accident

561
00:56:10,084 --> 00:56:12,754
if he sees the dead
for the first time so unexpectedly.

562
00:56:13,838 --> 00:56:14,708
You think so?

563
00:56:17,300 --> 00:56:19,970
I can't let him die from shock.
That'll complicate things.

564
00:56:32,481 --> 00:56:34,531
Excuse me, I was here first.

565
00:56:34,609 --> 00:56:36,439
That cab is mine, okay?

566
00:56:39,697 --> 00:56:42,067
You saw me standing here first all along.

567
00:56:45,286 --> 00:56:46,826
You saw me, right?

568
00:56:47,580 --> 00:56:48,920
I didn't.

569
00:56:49,957 --> 00:56:50,997
I can't see you.

570
00:56:55,379 --> 00:56:56,459
<i>Happy birthday.</i>

571
00:56:56,547 --> 00:57:00,007
<i>This year's present is going to be
a very special one.</i>

572
00:57:00,426 --> 00:57:03,386
<i>I saw a dead person there.</i>

573
00:57:05,973 --> 00:57:07,063
Where are you?

574
00:57:09,018 --> 00:57:10,018
Say something.

575
00:57:17,485 --> 00:57:19,445
Hey, are you going to get in or not?

576
00:57:20,363 --> 00:57:21,363
I'm getting in.

577
00:57:43,219 --> 00:57:45,349
He got one of the scariest ones
for the first one.

578
00:57:55,606 --> 00:57:57,436
Where should I go?

579
00:58:20,006 --> 00:58:23,006
Don't come here. Please.

580
00:59:05,926 --> 00:59:08,176
Why do you keep following me?

581
00:59:09,722 --> 00:59:11,022
Go away. Go.

582
00:59:11,682 --> 00:59:12,682
Go.

583
00:59:13,142 --> 00:59:14,192
Go!

584
00:59:15,978 --> 00:59:17,808
She's too harsh on him.

585
00:59:17,938 --> 00:59:19,518
Go!

586
00:59:19,607 --> 00:59:21,817
She'll make poor Chan-sung faint.

587
00:59:22,109 --> 00:59:24,109
Go!

588
00:59:26,197 --> 00:59:27,367
Don't take them off!

589
00:59:27,448 --> 00:59:28,868
Don't take off your sunglasses.

590
00:59:29,408 --> 00:59:30,788
I know you don't have any eyes.

591
00:59:30,951 --> 00:59:32,951
You look too scary without them on.

592
00:59:33,204 --> 00:59:36,834
Go!

593
01:00:17,331 --> 01:00:18,791
I guess you're traveling far.

594
01:00:25,423 --> 01:00:26,423
Yes.

595
01:00:27,216 --> 01:00:29,006
The present I gave you this time

596
01:00:29,218 --> 01:00:32,138
won't get caught at customs
at international airports.

597
01:00:32,304 --> 01:00:33,814
You won't be able to get rid of it.

598
01:00:34,306 --> 01:00:35,346
It's too bad.

599
01:00:35,724 --> 01:00:38,194
Are you the one who sent me
that strange thing earlier?

600
01:00:38,727 --> 01:00:41,807
No, I didn't send anything.
You're just able to see it.

601
01:00:43,023 --> 01:00:45,113
You're just starting to see things

602
01:00:45,484 --> 01:00:46,824
that you weren't able to earlier.

603
01:00:47,778 --> 01:00:48,698
And what is that?

604
01:00:49,155 --> 01:00:50,105
Ghosts.

605
01:00:54,160 --> 01:00:55,330
Damn it.

606
01:00:56,162 --> 01:00:58,712
There's a famous restaurant
around here that was on television.

607
01:00:58,956 --> 01:01:00,166
Let's go there.

608
01:01:00,916 --> 01:01:01,746
A restaurant?

609
01:01:01,834 --> 01:01:03,924
The one I always wanted to go to.
So this is great.

610
01:01:04,670 --> 01:01:06,210
What are you doing? Let's go.

611
01:01:08,382 --> 01:01:09,802
If I don't go with you now,

612
01:01:10,926 --> 01:01:13,006
will something like what I saw earlier
come to kill me?

613
01:01:13,137 --> 01:01:14,307
You won't die.

614
01:01:14,847 --> 01:01:17,347
What you saw earlier has no power
to kill the living.

615
01:01:17,850 --> 01:01:20,060
Not unless your feeble heart
fails from being startled.

616
01:01:20,352 --> 01:01:21,402
Happy?

617
01:01:22,563 --> 01:01:24,613
That restaurant closes soon. Let's hurry.

618
01:01:25,149 --> 01:01:26,319
Forget the restaurant.

619
01:01:26,400 --> 01:01:27,900
Turn my eyes back to normal.

620
01:01:27,985 --> 01:01:29,815
I won't go anywhere before you do that.

621
01:01:34,366 --> 01:01:37,406
If we don't get there
before the closing time because of you,

622
01:01:38,621 --> 01:01:41,081
I'll close your eyes for good.

623
01:01:44,460 --> 01:01:46,050
Forever.

624
01:01:55,346 --> 01:01:56,556
Open your eyes.

625
01:01:56,722 --> 01:01:58,892
Humans die when they starve.

626
01:01:59,141 --> 01:02:01,191
I brought you here so you won't die.

627
01:02:01,393 --> 01:02:03,943
Do you know the show
<i>The Guys Who Died After Eating</i>?

628
01:02:04,355 --> 01:02:07,185
This restaurant is where they came
to eat 30 orders of dumplings.

629
01:02:08,567 --> 01:02:09,857
You can't eat them if you come late.

630
01:02:13,572 --> 01:02:14,822
OUT OF INGREDIENTS

631
01:02:14,907 --> 01:02:15,947
See?

632
01:02:16,116 --> 01:02:18,576
If we'd been any later,
there wouldn't have been any food left.

633
01:02:23,332 --> 01:02:25,332
Gosh, I better move that thing away.

634
01:02:58,576 --> 01:03:01,196
It's the wench who shot a bullet at me.

635
01:03:08,294 --> 01:03:11,964
Do I have to look at such scary things
all the time?

636
01:03:12,047 --> 01:03:13,757
You were just unlucky.

637
01:03:13,841 --> 01:03:16,051
You ended up seeing
one of the most hideous ones.

638
01:03:16,260 --> 01:03:17,850
Not all of them are as scary.

639
01:03:19,972 --> 01:03:22,022
Right. Him. Look at him.

640
01:03:22,933 --> 01:03:24,643
Someone like him isn't so scary.

641
01:03:25,185 --> 01:03:27,435
If you only get a glimpse,

642
01:03:27,521 --> 01:03:29,731
you might just pass along
thinking he's a human.

643
01:03:30,691 --> 01:03:33,571
Most of them are like him,
so don't be scared.

644
01:03:34,069 --> 01:03:35,489
What is he doing over there?

645
01:03:35,571 --> 01:03:36,571
Some of them wander around

646
01:03:36,655 --> 01:03:38,865
because they don't know they're dead yet.

647
01:03:39,700 --> 01:03:42,160
Some of them get obsessed
with what they liked

648
01:03:42,244 --> 01:03:43,704
when they were alive.

649
01:03:44,830 --> 01:03:46,080
Is he obsessed with dumplings?

650
01:03:46,707 --> 01:03:47,707
It's hard to tell.

651
01:03:48,000 --> 01:03:50,000
Why did you make me see such a thing?

652
01:03:51,462 --> 01:03:53,422
You'll find out
when you come to Hotel del Luna.

653
01:03:56,050 --> 01:03:58,510
Why didn't you come when I told you to?

654
01:03:58,594 --> 01:04:00,894
Then you wouldn't have to go through
all this trouble.

655
01:04:01,430 --> 01:04:02,470
Gosh, that's hot.

656
01:04:03,974 --> 01:04:05,894
This is so hot.

657
01:04:06,101 --> 01:04:08,441
How did Kim Jun-hyun eat
five of these in one bite?

658
01:04:08,979 --> 01:04:10,609
He amazed me.

659
01:04:12,983 --> 01:04:14,033
You should try it too.

660
01:04:14,902 --> 01:04:16,862
You're the amazing one.

661
01:04:17,404 --> 01:04:19,954
At a glimpse and even up close,
you look like a normal person.

662
01:04:20,032 --> 01:04:21,412
Are you sure you're dead too?

663
01:04:24,370 --> 01:04:25,700
I'm not dead.

664
01:04:26,914 --> 01:04:28,084
I still haven't died.

665
01:04:29,333 --> 01:04:30,463
I'm just here.

666
01:04:38,175 --> 01:04:41,595
What do you mean, "still"?
Do you mean you might die one day?

667
01:04:41,887 --> 01:04:43,217
Why do you ask?

668
01:04:44,056 --> 01:04:46,806
Will you try to kill me?

669
01:04:53,357 --> 01:04:54,777
Try eating them all at once.

670
01:04:55,567 --> 01:04:57,357
If you succeed, I'll give you a chance.

671
01:05:02,533 --> 01:05:03,663
I just...

672
01:05:05,077 --> 01:05:07,537
want you to disappear from my sight.

673
01:05:21,427 --> 01:05:23,507
Koo Chan-sung,
the one who hates the sight of me.

674
01:05:24,221 --> 01:05:26,931
Go across the street
and buy me a milk tea.

675
01:05:27,182 --> 01:05:29,182
After she ate that many dumplings?

676
01:05:29,476 --> 01:05:31,306
Was she really amazed by Jun-hyun?

677
01:05:31,687 --> 01:05:33,057
Is she really not a human?

678
01:05:33,313 --> 01:05:34,403
Hurry up.

679
01:05:34,857 --> 01:05:36,687
If it closes because you're late,
you'll die.

680
01:06:05,971 --> 01:06:08,101
You're the one who shot me, aren't you?

681
01:06:08,307 --> 01:06:09,557
I'm sure you shot me.

682
01:06:12,227 --> 01:06:14,607
You look horrible just like your crimes.

683
01:06:15,773 --> 01:06:18,073
You can look forward to your afterlife.

684
01:06:18,734 --> 01:06:20,114
It'll be even worse.

685
01:06:24,990 --> 01:06:26,580
It's all your fault.

686
01:06:27,075 --> 01:06:28,195
It's your fault.

687
01:06:32,289 --> 01:06:34,999
Die!

688
01:07:06,198 --> 01:07:07,278
What's going on?

689
01:07:20,045 --> 01:07:21,955
Were you stabbed?

690
01:07:23,298 --> 01:07:25,588
Why is it that humans...

691
01:07:26,969 --> 01:07:29,759
never think about their wrongs
and only blame others?

692
01:07:29,847 --> 01:07:30,967
I asked if you are okay.

693
01:07:36,270 --> 01:07:39,520
I don't dare mock that dirty old man.

694
01:07:41,859 --> 01:07:43,689
I was once just as crazy...

695
01:07:44,987 --> 01:07:46,697
and carried a sword with me.

696
01:07:48,657 --> 01:07:49,867
Koo Chan-sung.

697
01:07:50,075 --> 01:07:53,115
You failed to eat those dumplings all
at once, but I'll still give you a chance.

698
01:07:55,247 --> 01:07:56,827
If you want to run away, go.

699
01:08:03,964 --> 01:08:06,224
If you turn around and walk away now,

700
01:08:08,093 --> 01:08:09,933
I'll disappear from your sight...

701
01:08:11,763 --> 01:08:13,933
just as you wanted.

702
01:08:18,145 --> 01:08:19,145
Go.

703
01:08:30,616 --> 01:08:32,576
If you don't leave now, it'll be too late.

704
01:09:34,262 --> 01:09:35,312
What is this?

705
01:09:35,389 --> 01:09:37,519
I'll help you get up. Get on this cart.

706
01:09:38,600 --> 01:09:41,440
I'll take you to a hospital
or Hotel del Luna.

707
01:09:41,937 --> 01:09:43,057
Hurry.

708
01:09:45,607 --> 01:09:46,527
What are you doing?

709
01:09:46,608 --> 01:09:48,778
I don't have the energy
to carry you in my arms.

710
01:09:48,902 --> 01:09:50,452
This thing isn't dirty, so get on.

711
01:10:03,875 --> 01:10:04,995
This is...

712
01:10:11,675 --> 01:10:12,795
Are you okay?

713
01:10:12,884 --> 01:10:14,014
Koo Chan-sung.

714
01:10:15,470 --> 01:10:17,390
You're really...

715
01:10:19,850 --> 01:10:21,230
weak, aren't you?

716
01:10:28,775 --> 01:10:31,275
You dragged this cart over for me.

717
01:10:31,611 --> 01:10:34,071
I like your feeble heart...

718
01:10:35,157 --> 01:10:36,277
very much.

719
01:10:36,450 --> 01:10:38,490
It's amazing knife stabs can't hurt you.

720
01:10:38,660 --> 01:10:40,660
I guess this weak human wasted his time.

721
01:10:41,246 --> 01:10:43,416
I'll go on my way, then.

722
01:10:44,207 --> 01:10:45,207
You can't go.

723
01:11:04,686 --> 01:11:05,976
What are you doing?

724
01:11:17,908 --> 01:11:19,078
You...

725
01:11:19,826 --> 01:11:21,116
Are you really trying to...

726
01:12:05,705 --> 01:12:09,205
I gave you the chance to run away,
but you gave that up.

727
01:12:11,253 --> 01:12:13,003
If you run away now,

728
01:12:15,215 --> 01:12:16,415
I'll kill you.

729
01:13:03,471 --> 01:13:05,771
<i>What are you going
to make me do there anyway?</i>

730
01:13:05,849 --> 01:13:06,889
Exorcism?

731
01:13:06,975 --> 01:13:08,095
We don't perform an exorcism.

732
01:13:08,185 --> 01:13:10,015
We comfort them.

733
01:13:10,103 --> 01:13:11,983
<i>Wouldn't it be dangerous for me
to get too close?</i>

734
01:13:12,063 --> 01:13:14,613
Then address me properly. It's "Ms. Jang."

735
01:13:14,774 --> 01:13:16,404
With the Harvard MBA--

736
01:13:16,484 --> 01:13:17,494
You don't need an MBA.

737
01:13:17,569 --> 01:13:19,109
<i>You can see ghosts now.</i>

738
01:13:19,196 --> 01:13:22,446
How do you expect me to live a normal life
when I can see ghosts?

739
01:13:22,824 --> 01:13:25,624
Go and tell the chairman
that you can get rid of the tiger

740
01:13:25,702 --> 01:13:26,622
in return for something.

741
01:13:26,703 --> 01:13:28,123
<i>You said they're not dangerous.</i>

742
01:13:28,205 --> 01:13:31,205
Come to Hotel del Luna.
You'll be safe if you stay by my side.

743
01:13:33,710 --> 01:13:35,960
Subtitle translation by Wayne Ryu

744
01:14:06,088 --> 01:14:09,628
I gave you the chance to run away,
but you gave that up.

745
01:14:11,760 --> 01:14:13,390
If you run away now,

746
01:14:15,639 --> 01:14:16,719
I'll kill you.

747
01:14:22,687 --> 01:14:25,727
Did you just kill the old man
that attacked you earlier?

748
01:14:58,223 --> 01:14:59,063
What is this?

749
01:15:06,690 --> 01:15:07,690
What was that?

750
01:15:08,483 --> 01:15:10,743
The leftover ashes
of that revengeful ghost.

751
01:15:10,819 --> 01:15:12,529
Was he a ghost?

752
01:15:12,612 --> 01:15:15,242
I told you that some of them
look like humans.

753
01:15:15,365 --> 01:15:17,615
But you said they're not dangerous.

754
01:15:19,745 --> 01:15:21,745
If you get attacked by those
who hold deep grudges,

755
01:15:21,830 --> 01:15:23,290
you could end up getting killed.

756
01:15:23,874 --> 01:15:25,714
You should learn to differentiate them.

757
01:15:26,209 --> 01:15:27,959
But you said it's hard to tell them apart.

758
01:15:28,044 --> 01:15:30,344
That's why you need to look closely.

759
01:15:30,422 --> 01:15:32,012
I get scared if I look...

760
01:15:32,549 --> 01:15:33,379
too closely.

761
01:15:35,427 --> 01:15:37,347
What are you scared of?
I'm right by your side.

762
01:15:39,598 --> 01:15:40,598
Wait!

763
01:15:43,393 --> 01:15:44,393
Can you...

764
01:15:46,688 --> 01:15:47,858
get that for me?

765
01:15:51,693 --> 01:15:53,903
Wouldn't it be dangerous for me
to get too close?

766
01:15:54,404 --> 01:15:55,414
Hurry.

767
01:16:00,327 --> 01:16:03,037
Then address me properly. It's "Ms. Jang."

768
01:16:03,580 --> 01:16:05,290
You know, you're not my boss.

769
01:16:05,373 --> 01:16:07,633
I told you that I don't want
to work at your hotel.

770
01:16:07,792 --> 01:16:09,792
I guess you're not that scared yet.

771
01:16:18,887 --> 01:16:21,717
Hey, if we just leave that there,

772
01:16:21,806 --> 01:16:23,886
wouldn't it be dangerous
to the people passing by?

773
01:16:24,267 --> 01:16:26,557
That piece of trash
will soon get collected.

774
01:16:26,853 --> 01:16:27,693
By whom?

775
01:16:28,271 --> 01:16:29,401
The Grim Reaper.

776
01:16:32,484 --> 01:16:33,904
You're going to wear that again?

777
01:16:35,362 --> 01:16:36,202
Why?

778
01:16:37,405 --> 01:16:38,485
Is it dangerous?

779
01:16:39,074 --> 01:16:40,584
But it's practically new.

780
01:16:40,992 --> 01:16:42,662
Can't I just wipe it and wear it again?

781
01:16:43,161 --> 01:16:45,751
Throw it away.
Let's go get you a new pair of shoes.

782
01:16:58,426 --> 01:16:59,676
Where's my luggage bag?

783
01:17:04,057 --> 01:17:06,427
DEATH

784
01:17:16,111 --> 01:17:20,201
Let's see.

785
01:17:22,158 --> 01:17:23,028
They look nice.

786
01:17:23,159 --> 01:17:24,119
Wear those.

787
01:17:25,662 --> 01:17:28,422
No, they're not my style.

788
01:17:29,249 --> 01:17:31,959
They're way better than the tacky
poop-colored ones you had earlier.

789
01:17:32,836 --> 01:17:34,336
Don't ever wear stuff like that.

790
01:17:34,462 --> 01:17:35,762
I hate that color.

791
01:17:37,465 --> 01:17:40,085
Then, did you tell me
to throw that shoe away because--

792
01:17:40,176 --> 01:17:41,796
Because it was tacky and poop-colored.

793
01:17:42,137 --> 01:17:43,507
Not because it was dangerous?

794
01:17:43,889 --> 01:17:47,179
I never said it was dangerous.

795
01:17:48,685 --> 01:17:50,725
If you don't like those, wear these.

796
01:17:53,023 --> 01:17:54,023
No.

797
01:17:54,774 --> 01:17:58,034
I'm going to choose
exactly the same one as earlier.

798
01:17:58,695 --> 01:18:01,445
Just wear them.
The store's going to close soon.

799
01:18:01,615 --> 01:18:02,525
Forget it.

800
01:18:05,076 --> 01:18:07,366
Thank you for coming to our store.

801
01:18:07,454 --> 01:18:08,504
My goodness.

802
01:18:10,206 --> 01:18:13,996
I didn't even get to buy my shoes
because you were being so fussy.

803
01:18:14,085 --> 01:18:15,335
If we had more time,

804
01:18:15,420 --> 01:18:17,880
I would never have bought these.

805
01:18:18,214 --> 01:18:19,934
Well, that's too bad.

806
01:18:20,216 --> 01:18:22,046
Every place has a closing time.

807
01:18:23,178 --> 01:18:26,178
I bought you the new shoes,
so start working from tomorrow.

808
01:18:26,431 --> 01:18:27,641
Let's get the facts straight.

809
01:18:27,724 --> 01:18:30,444
You picked whatever you wanted,
and I'm the one who bought them.

810
01:18:30,644 --> 01:18:32,654
And I'm not going to work at your hotel.

811
01:18:32,979 --> 01:18:35,189
What are you going
to make me do there anyway?

812
01:18:47,369 --> 01:18:50,959
You'll be consoling the ones
who closed the doors with frustration.

813
01:18:52,207 --> 01:18:53,207
Closed what doors?

814
01:18:53,291 --> 01:18:56,251
Closed the doors to their lives.

815
01:19:09,432 --> 01:19:10,522
Death.

816
01:19:29,828 --> 01:19:30,948
Mr. Kim Byeong-du.

817
01:19:35,750 --> 01:19:37,040
I've come to escort you.

818
01:20:00,316 --> 01:20:04,026
You've started a long journey.

819
01:20:07,240 --> 01:20:11,200
I hope you safely cross
the bridge of the Samdo River.

820
01:21:17,185 --> 01:21:20,515
When people die in this world,
most of them cross the bridge

821
01:21:20,897 --> 01:21:22,977
over the Samdo River

822
01:21:23,316 --> 01:21:24,726
and go to another world.

823
01:21:26,778 --> 01:21:30,368
But some souls
fail to find their way there.

824
01:21:31,574 --> 01:21:32,744
You also saw some of them.

825
01:21:34,828 --> 01:21:36,998
Those who foolishly stay in this world

826
01:21:38,164 --> 01:21:41,254
even when their lives here have ended.

827
01:21:48,174 --> 01:21:49,974
Just like how you're standing here

828
01:21:50,218 --> 01:21:52,548
even when the department store
has already closed?

829
01:21:53,930 --> 01:21:55,140
Good metaphor.

830
01:21:56,057 --> 01:21:57,267
You understood it very well.

831
01:21:57,934 --> 01:21:59,314
Those who come to my hotel

832
01:21:59,477 --> 01:22:02,807
are souls who got lost
on their way to the afterlife.

833
01:22:06,234 --> 01:22:10,114
So you're saying your hotel guests
are all ghosts.

834
01:22:11,197 --> 01:22:13,317
And that's why you made me see them.

835
01:22:14,951 --> 01:22:16,081
Come to Hotel del Luna.

836
01:22:17,078 --> 01:22:18,868
You'll be safe if you stay by my side.

837
01:22:28,798 --> 01:22:32,638
The most dangerous thing you can do is
to try and run away without permission.

838
01:22:33,344 --> 01:22:34,354
Don't do it.

839
01:22:42,437 --> 01:22:45,107
Koo Chan-sung,
wear your new shoes tomorrow

840
01:22:45,398 --> 01:22:48,608
and make sure you get on subway Line Four.

841
01:22:52,238 --> 01:22:53,238
Jang Man-wol.

842
01:22:55,450 --> 01:22:58,620
I told you to refer to me
as your boss. Call me "Ms. Jang."

843
01:22:58,912 --> 01:22:59,912
What about you?

844
01:23:00,705 --> 01:23:02,075
Where do you stand?

845
01:23:04,125 --> 01:23:05,415
Is your door not shut yet?

846
01:23:06,586 --> 01:23:09,206
Or are you one of those hanging around
after their doors are shut?

847
01:23:19,474 --> 01:23:21,604
You're not a normal human being like me.

848
01:23:21,851 --> 01:23:23,771
I can tell that much
from what I experienced today.

849
01:23:24,395 --> 01:23:27,645
You said those who hold deep grudges
can kill people.

850
01:23:28,775 --> 01:23:30,685
You said you could kill me.

851
01:23:31,194 --> 01:23:32,904
Does that make you a vengeful ghost too?

852
01:23:36,407 --> 01:23:37,777
The one

853
01:23:38,660 --> 01:23:40,950
standing right beside you now is
probably a vengeful ghost.

854
01:23:45,917 --> 01:23:47,497
You shut your mouth right away.

855
01:23:49,212 --> 01:23:51,462
I knew it. You're totally my cup of tea.

856
01:23:54,467 --> 01:23:55,467
Gosh, I'm...

857
01:24:15,405 --> 01:24:16,815
"A vengeful ghost"?

858
01:24:31,462 --> 01:24:34,382
Here you go. I'll give you more.

859
01:24:34,465 --> 01:24:35,875
Let's eat. Come here.

860
01:24:37,176 --> 01:24:38,176
Come on.

861
01:24:55,903 --> 01:24:57,493
Kitties, eat more.

862
01:25:00,074 --> 01:25:01,164
Yun-seo.

863
01:25:02,160 --> 01:25:03,290
Yun-seo.

864
01:25:35,318 --> 01:25:36,688
Meow.

865
01:25:37,570 --> 01:25:39,950
A big cat. You're a big cat.

866
01:25:47,663 --> 01:25:48,923
Yun-seo.

867
01:25:49,791 --> 01:25:51,541
What were you staring at?

868
01:25:51,626 --> 01:25:53,996
Meow. I saw a big cat.

869
01:25:55,963 --> 01:25:58,013
I was so worried about you.

870
01:26:07,642 --> 01:26:10,272
Is this tree alive or dead?

871
01:26:11,270 --> 01:26:15,320
It hasn't grown a single leaf
or flower for over a millennium.

872
01:26:15,817 --> 01:26:17,317
Does it mean it's dead?

873
01:26:18,277 --> 01:26:20,447
Where do you stand?

874
01:26:21,197 --> 01:26:22,487
Is your door not shut yet?

875
01:26:23,616 --> 01:26:26,326
Or are you one of those hanging around
after their doors are shut?

876
01:26:27,954 --> 01:26:29,874
It is still alive.

877
01:26:30,832 --> 01:26:31,832
You said

878
01:26:32,667 --> 01:26:35,037
that this tree is like your second self.

879
01:26:36,838 --> 01:26:41,378
Right, so can we say that I am alive?

880
01:26:44,220 --> 01:26:47,680
I prepared a great bottle of champagne
for you.

881
01:26:47,765 --> 01:26:49,175
Would you like some now?

882
01:26:50,226 --> 01:26:53,346
Sure, not just a bottle though.
I want a whole crate.

883
01:26:59,110 --> 01:27:00,360
Someone's here.

884
01:27:03,447 --> 01:27:06,117
A very special guest is here.

885
01:27:08,286 --> 01:27:09,656
I should go welcome the guest.

886
01:27:38,983 --> 01:27:41,073
Ms. Jang, wasn't that a tiger?

887
01:27:41,152 --> 01:27:42,402
It's dangerous

888
01:27:43,488 --> 01:27:46,158
for a soul of a mystical creature
to be wandering like that.

889
01:27:46,866 --> 01:27:48,366
Did you kick out the tiger?

890
01:27:50,161 --> 01:27:52,211
Can't you do your job better?

891
01:27:53,331 --> 01:27:55,421
You should've sensed it
and welcomed the guest.

892
01:27:55,500 --> 01:27:57,380
I've been working here for almost 60 years

893
01:27:57,460 --> 01:27:59,210
but never seen a tiger coming as a guest.

894
01:27:59,295 --> 01:28:00,455
Do your job properly.

895
01:28:00,880 --> 01:28:04,430
A ton of ghosts want to work here
to stay in the living realm.

896
01:28:04,675 --> 01:28:07,345
If you have complaints,
just get on the bus to the afterlife.

897
01:28:07,553 --> 01:28:08,433
I won't stop you.

898
01:28:08,513 --> 01:28:11,603
I got Koo Chan-sung involved
because I'm bad at my job, you know.

899
01:28:11,807 --> 01:28:14,477
I'm not that competent,
but I'm quite lucky.

900
01:28:14,560 --> 01:28:16,520
Did you die young because you're so lucky?

901
01:28:18,481 --> 01:28:20,481
Gosh, she's so mean.

902
01:28:20,942 --> 01:28:23,112
Ms. Jang, I'll work harder!

903
01:28:24,570 --> 01:28:26,450
DEAR KOO CHAN-SUNG, HAPPY BIRTHDAY

904
01:28:29,700 --> 01:28:31,120
Hey, when did you get here?

905
01:28:32,161 --> 01:28:33,621
Didn't you say you were going somewhere?

906
01:28:33,996 --> 01:28:36,746
I was so excited when you told me
you'd stay at my place,

907
01:28:36,832 --> 01:28:38,792
then disappointed
thinking you were leaving again.

908
01:28:38,876 --> 01:28:40,246
Hey, let's have a welcome party.

909
01:28:40,336 --> 01:28:43,206
What do you want to drink?
Beer, hard liquor, or soju, pick one.

910
01:28:46,133 --> 01:28:47,343
Why are you all quiet?

911
01:28:49,345 --> 01:28:50,345
Chan-sung.

912
01:28:51,472 --> 01:28:53,142
Hey, Chan-sung.

913
01:28:55,601 --> 01:28:57,771
You're not even answering me.
Let's have beer, then.

914
01:29:00,690 --> 01:29:02,110
YOU'VE BEEN HIRED BY HOTEL DEL LUNA

915
01:29:03,276 --> 01:29:04,896
Does that make you a vengeful ghost too?

916
01:29:09,365 --> 01:29:11,195
Was that too mean?

917
01:29:48,738 --> 01:29:50,908
I saw a glamorous sign flashing,

918
01:29:51,282 --> 01:29:53,492
and it was covered with ivy
on the outside.

919
01:29:53,868 --> 01:29:55,658
It was a fabulous-looking hotel.

920
01:29:58,706 --> 01:30:00,286
"Hotel del Luna."

921
01:30:01,500 --> 01:30:03,340
It looks more ordinary than I expected.

922
01:30:20,728 --> 01:30:22,148
Is it closed during the day?

923
01:30:25,775 --> 01:30:27,065
I scared you, didn't I?

924
01:30:29,236 --> 01:30:30,816
You're not dead.

925
01:30:32,156 --> 01:30:35,486
-No.
-Look at our rates and decide.

926
01:30:40,122 --> 01:30:41,542
ROOM RATES

927
01:30:42,208 --> 01:30:44,838
Your rooms are ridiculously expensive.

928
01:30:44,919 --> 01:30:46,709
Yes. They're very expensive, aren't they?

929
01:30:46,837 --> 01:30:49,127
But we must abide by our rules,
so no discount is allowed.

930
01:30:49,215 --> 01:30:50,875
You sound like you don't want me
as a guest.

931
01:30:51,467 --> 01:30:54,797
With that amount of money, you can stay
at the five-star hotel nearby.

932
01:30:55,304 --> 01:30:57,774
I would've done that
if I had come here as a guest,

933
01:30:58,599 --> 01:30:59,889
but I'm not here as a guest.

934
01:31:04,647 --> 01:31:05,727
"Dear Koo..."

935
01:31:08,150 --> 01:31:10,320
You're the new manager, Mr. Koo Chan-sung.

936
01:31:10,403 --> 01:31:12,993
I haven't accepted the position.
I'm just visiting.

937
01:31:13,072 --> 01:31:14,452
Ms. Jang is waiting for you.

938
01:31:14,532 --> 01:31:16,332
You can go up this way, Mr. Manager.

939
01:31:17,660 --> 01:31:19,080
I'm not a manager.

940
01:31:19,161 --> 01:31:20,871
Okay, sure. This way, please.

941
01:31:56,449 --> 01:31:57,989
Are there no guests at the moment?

942
01:31:58,784 --> 01:31:59,794
All the rooms are full.

943
01:31:59,869 --> 01:32:01,999
But it's quiet
because most of them are asleep.

944
01:32:03,456 --> 01:32:05,166
It's more ordinary than what I've heard.

945
01:32:05,249 --> 01:32:07,839
I've heard this hotel has
a sealike outdoor pool and a rooftop bar.

946
01:32:07,918 --> 01:32:09,458
We take pride in those two facilities.

947
01:32:10,713 --> 01:32:11,763
So you actually have them?

948
01:32:11,839 --> 01:32:13,089
Would you like to take a look,

949
01:32:13,424 --> 01:32:14,434
Mr. Manager?

950
01:32:14,508 --> 01:32:16,218
No, thanks. I don't need to see them.

951
01:32:17,636 --> 01:32:19,466
And I told you
I'm not the manager of this hotel.

952
01:32:19,555 --> 01:32:21,265
Then shall I call you Chan-sung?

953
01:32:21,932 --> 01:32:23,352
Mr. Koo Chan-sung.

954
01:32:27,229 --> 01:32:29,149
Ms. Jang is waiting for you.

955
01:32:38,449 --> 01:32:41,789
You can think
that it's around 3 a.m. here now

956
01:32:41,869 --> 01:32:43,749
for a regular hotel.

957
01:32:44,288 --> 01:32:45,788
He said all the rooms are occupied.

958
01:32:46,749 --> 01:32:48,419
So, they're all occupied by ghosts?

959
01:33:02,348 --> 01:33:04,228
I'm a human

960
01:33:04,975 --> 01:33:07,135
just like you.

961
01:33:30,876 --> 01:33:32,036
She's been alive...

962
01:33:33,838 --> 01:33:35,008
ever since then...

963
01:33:36,507 --> 01:33:37,967
until now?

964
01:33:48,811 --> 01:33:50,401
She'll be here soon.

965
01:33:51,730 --> 01:33:52,690
Excuse me.

966
01:33:53,357 --> 01:33:54,897
Have you been working here
for a long time?

967
01:33:55,442 --> 01:33:58,072
I started working here when I turned 40.

968
01:33:58,320 --> 01:34:00,070
So it's been over 30 years.

969
01:34:00,656 --> 01:34:02,406
What? 30 years?

970
01:34:02,491 --> 01:34:05,661
I'm the only person
who ages in this hotel.

971
01:34:07,997 --> 01:34:14,127
And now, you'll be taking over my job.

972
01:34:21,969 --> 01:34:23,219
For 30 years?

973
01:34:25,681 --> 01:34:28,061
Does that mean I need to be here
until I become that old?

974
01:34:32,521 --> 01:34:33,521
Why are you so late?

975
01:34:36,108 --> 01:34:39,108
You're not wearing the shoes
I picked out for you yesterday.

976
01:34:42,406 --> 01:34:44,116
Those shoes are too flashy to wear

977
01:34:44,199 --> 01:34:46,739
at the hotel I currently work at.

978
01:34:46,994 --> 01:34:50,044
I just dropped by.
I need to go to work soon.

979
01:34:51,081 --> 01:34:53,581
The girl wearing sunglasses
must've gone easy on you.

980
01:34:54,251 --> 01:34:56,921
You're the one who made her
follow me around?

981
01:34:57,212 --> 01:34:59,672
You made her follow me around
when she has no grudge against me?

982
01:34:59,798 --> 01:35:00,878
Oh, that.

983
01:35:01,091 --> 01:35:04,011
She's hovering around the person
she's had a connection with.

984
01:35:04,136 --> 01:35:05,596
Once they form a connection,

985
01:35:05,679 --> 01:35:08,059
the connection
automatically lasts forever.

986
01:35:08,182 --> 01:35:10,182
Do you think I'm a wireless router
or something?

987
01:35:11,560 --> 01:35:12,850
That's a great metaphor.

988
01:35:13,062 --> 01:35:16,192
You understand things very well.
I'm starting to like you even more.

989
01:35:16,482 --> 01:35:18,322
I don't want you to like me.

990
01:35:18,400 --> 01:35:19,820
And I hate seeing those ghosts.

991
01:35:19,902 --> 01:35:20,942
You need to see them.

992
01:35:21,570 --> 01:35:23,030
And you'd better get used to it.

993
01:35:23,113 --> 01:35:26,913
Those ghosts will be your guests
from now on.

994
01:35:29,119 --> 01:35:30,869
Is this a new kind of religion
or something?

995
01:35:30,954 --> 01:35:34,044
Is this a house owned by a shaman
who takes care of ghosts?

996
01:35:34,124 --> 01:35:35,174
It's a hotel.

997
01:35:36,001 --> 01:35:38,091
It's even registered
at the Jung-gu District office.

998
01:35:38,587 --> 01:35:40,087
JUNG-GU DISTRICT OFFICE, SEOUL

999
01:35:40,172 --> 01:35:42,012
BUSINESS REGISTRATION
HOTEL DEL LUNA

1000
01:35:43,050 --> 01:35:45,260
I searched the web all night
to find the hotel website.

1001
01:35:45,344 --> 01:35:46,514
But I couldn't find

1002
01:35:46,595 --> 01:35:49,135
a single website or post
regarding Hotel del Luna.

1003
01:35:49,223 --> 01:35:52,233
Of course, you couldn't find
a hotel website.

1004
01:35:52,434 --> 01:35:55,194
I told you
that this hotel isn't for humans.

1005
01:35:58,190 --> 01:35:59,940
You said this place
consoles ghosts, right?

1006
01:36:01,193 --> 01:36:04,073
Then what kind of services
do you provide for your guests?

1007
01:36:04,154 --> 01:36:05,534
Exorcism?

1008
01:36:05,656 --> 01:36:06,946
We don't perform an exorcism.

1009
01:36:07,533 --> 01:36:09,203
We comfort them.

1010
01:36:27,928 --> 01:36:29,808
It's the room service.

1011
01:36:37,020 --> 01:36:39,820
Eat everything you couldn't eat
while you were alive.

1012
01:36:40,858 --> 01:36:43,568
We have all kinds of food you want.

1013
01:37:06,842 --> 01:37:07,892
Sir.

1014
01:37:08,343 --> 01:37:10,143
Do you feel warm now?

1015
01:37:18,854 --> 01:37:20,614
I'll burn the firewood for you

1016
01:37:20,856 --> 01:37:23,026
until you become warm.

1017
01:37:36,371 --> 01:37:38,251
You're even reading
the original copies now.

1018
01:37:39,082 --> 01:37:41,422
You'll soon end up reading
every single book in this room.

1019
01:37:41,794 --> 01:37:43,254
Study as much as you want.

1020
01:37:45,672 --> 01:37:49,222
I'll get you
whatever book you want to read.

1021
01:37:49,301 --> 01:37:51,261
Thank you.

1022
01:37:52,971 --> 01:37:57,061
Hotel del Luna is a place
where souls who used to be humans

1023
01:37:57,309 --> 01:38:00,599
come to rest and do things
that they failed to fulfill

1024
01:38:00,687 --> 01:38:02,187
while they were alive.

1025
01:38:04,358 --> 01:38:07,188
In other words, it's a place
where they comfort themselves.

1026
01:38:08,403 --> 01:38:10,413
Humans are not the only ones
who need that.

1027
01:38:10,489 --> 01:38:14,029
Ghosts need to do it too
in order to leave with no regrets.

1028
01:38:15,619 --> 01:38:18,249
The guests are ghosts,
so the manager should be a ghost as well.

1029
01:38:18,330 --> 01:38:19,870
Why do you need someone who's human?

1030
01:38:19,957 --> 01:38:22,917
Because there are things
that only humans can do.

1031
01:38:23,585 --> 01:38:25,835
Register our business
at the district office, pay taxes,

1032
01:38:25,921 --> 01:38:28,131
receive hygiene inspections, and so on.

1033
01:38:28,298 --> 01:38:30,008
There are so many things you have to do.

1034
01:38:30,634 --> 01:38:32,594
I want to deal with this
like a normal human being.

1035
01:38:36,306 --> 01:38:39,136
This is the money I've saved up
to pay you back.

1036
01:38:39,434 --> 01:38:42,104
It's the money you gave my dad,
plus interest.

1037
01:38:42,187 --> 01:38:43,647
Take this and let me go.

1038
01:38:56,326 --> 01:38:57,696
You saved up quite a lot.

1039
01:38:59,037 --> 01:39:01,667
You're very diligent and clever.

1040
01:39:03,083 --> 01:39:05,043
I guess I won't need to worry
about losing money.

1041
01:39:05,794 --> 01:39:08,054
I'll take it since you gave it to me.

1042
01:39:11,133 --> 01:39:13,683
Then that means we're even.

1043
01:39:15,220 --> 01:39:16,390
I'll be off now.

1044
01:39:16,471 --> 01:39:17,391
Okay.

1045
01:39:17,848 --> 01:39:20,268
I was actually waiting for you
so we could leave together.

1046
01:39:20,601 --> 01:39:21,481
Let's go.

1047
01:39:21,560 --> 01:39:24,310
I didn't plan on leaving with you.

1048
01:39:24,438 --> 01:39:26,148
You're going to leave by yourself?

1049
01:39:26,398 --> 01:39:27,228
Yes.

1050
01:39:28,942 --> 01:39:30,072
Okay, then.

1051
01:39:30,944 --> 01:39:31,904
Go ahead.

1052
01:40:07,773 --> 01:40:09,153
The third floor, please.

1053
01:40:09,650 --> 01:40:10,650
Okay.

1054
01:40:46,895 --> 01:40:48,015
Why?

1055
01:40:48,647 --> 01:40:52,027
Why am I still seeing ghosts?

1056
01:40:52,901 --> 01:40:55,401
I paid you back, so I shouldn't be seeing
them anymore.

1057
01:40:55,779 --> 01:40:57,489
You just paid back what you owe me.

1058
01:40:58,073 --> 01:40:59,953
And what I gave you was a birthday gift.

1059
01:41:00,534 --> 01:41:01,624
You should

1060
01:41:02,411 --> 01:41:03,701
cherish it.

1061
01:41:03,787 --> 01:41:04,997
Are you kidding me?

1062
01:41:05,789 --> 01:41:09,919
How do you expect me to live a normal life
when I can see ghosts?

1063
01:41:10,002 --> 01:41:13,052
Then I guess you have no choice
but to work here.

1064
01:41:14,214 --> 01:41:16,844
Return my eyes back to normal.

1065
01:41:19,177 --> 01:41:21,557
I'm going to head out. What do you say?

1066
01:41:21,722 --> 01:41:22,932
Are you going to come with me?

1067
01:41:24,683 --> 01:41:25,853
Stay here if you don't want to.

1068
01:41:27,019 --> 01:41:28,729
Let's continue our conversation

1069
01:41:30,647 --> 01:41:31,937
once we're out of here.

1070
01:41:49,833 --> 01:41:53,883
The new guy looks very weakhearted.
I'm starting to get worried.

1071
01:41:53,962 --> 01:41:56,472
He looks very courageous to me.

1072
01:42:01,595 --> 01:42:04,675
I was more scared of Ms. Jang
than the ghosts.

1073
01:42:04,931 --> 01:42:05,931
But

1074
01:42:06,266 --> 01:42:10,016
he seems to have no trouble
talking to Ms. Jang.

1075
01:42:10,103 --> 01:42:12,443
That's because he doesn't know
why Ms. Jang

1076
01:42:12,522 --> 01:42:13,902
is the owner of this place.

1077
01:42:15,150 --> 01:42:16,150
Hurry.

1078
01:42:18,278 --> 01:42:22,568
Among all the ghosts here,
she's the scariest and the most awful.

1079
01:42:37,547 --> 01:42:39,967
-This is your car, right?
-Today,

1080
01:42:40,050 --> 01:42:41,220
I'm going to drive this one.

1081
01:42:45,972 --> 01:42:48,562
Do you own all these cars?

1082
01:42:48,642 --> 01:42:50,982
I already told you
that all our guests are ghosts.

1083
01:42:51,061 --> 01:42:52,731
Do you think they drove here?

1084
01:43:10,247 --> 01:43:11,957
You have a lot of fancy cars.

1085
01:43:12,124 --> 01:43:15,004
Do I look like a human
now that you see I have a sports car?

1086
01:43:15,085 --> 01:43:16,205
I guess you earn

1087
01:43:18,130 --> 01:43:20,760
a lot of money
by comforting the dead souls.

1088
01:43:21,925 --> 01:43:24,215
You hate that you're seeing ghosts,

1089
01:43:24,302 --> 01:43:26,302
but you like fancy things
like this car, don't you?

1090
01:43:26,847 --> 01:43:28,097
Don't you want to work for me?

1091
01:43:28,223 --> 01:43:30,143
I can't understand
how you can accumulate wealth

1092
01:43:30,225 --> 01:43:32,685
by comforting them
in a supernatural sense.

1093
01:43:33,145 --> 01:43:36,145
You began to take interest
in the hotel's profit structure.

1094
01:43:36,356 --> 01:43:38,896
I should have shown you
my cars first instead of the ghosts.

1095
01:43:39,151 --> 01:43:40,281
I'm not interested.

1096
01:43:44,489 --> 01:43:45,369
Why are you laughing?

1097
01:43:45,449 --> 01:43:47,409
I find it funny
that a ghost wears a seat belt.

1098
01:43:49,119 --> 01:43:50,949
I will drive you to your destination.

1099
01:43:51,288 --> 01:43:52,538
But you must fix my eyes.

1100
01:43:54,082 --> 01:43:55,252
Why are you snickering?

1101
01:43:55,750 --> 01:43:56,750
I just

1102
01:43:56,960 --> 01:43:59,750
find it funny that you believe
that I'm going to fix your eyes.

1103
01:44:00,046 --> 01:44:01,376
We had a deal.

1104
01:44:01,506 --> 01:44:03,086
If you don't fix my eyes, I can't work.

1105
01:44:03,175 --> 01:44:04,255
Right, you can't go to work

1106
01:44:04,342 --> 01:44:06,302
because you need to take care
of something else now.

1107
01:44:07,596 --> 01:44:09,006
Where are we going now?

1108
01:44:12,601 --> 01:44:13,811
To catch a tiger.

1109
01:44:15,687 --> 01:44:17,107
You're kidding, right?

1110
01:44:37,083 --> 01:44:38,293
This was...

1111
01:44:40,045 --> 01:44:41,245
the tiger's life.

1112
01:44:42,255 --> 01:44:44,835
Can a tiger stay at your hotel?

1113
01:44:45,634 --> 01:44:47,014
It's a mystical creature, so yes.

1114
01:44:49,513 --> 01:44:53,183
This was the last Siberian tiger which was
captured on the Korean Peninsula.

1115
01:44:53,266 --> 01:44:55,636
I remember watching the news
about receiving the tiger

1116
01:44:55,727 --> 01:44:57,057
from North Korea as a gift.

1117
01:44:57,604 --> 01:45:00,024
The tiger neither got along
with other tigers,

1118
01:45:00,106 --> 01:45:01,396
nor mated with others.

1119
01:45:01,608 --> 01:45:03,528
The tiger stayed alone
until the last moment.

1120
01:45:04,778 --> 01:45:06,148
The tiger is dead,

1121
01:45:08,698 --> 01:45:10,778
but they made it look like it's alive...

1122
01:45:12,744 --> 01:45:14,204
and put it on display here.

1123
01:45:18,583 --> 01:45:19,833
I'm not dead.

1124
01:45:20,168 --> 01:45:21,418
I still haven't died.

1125
01:45:22,295 --> 01:45:23,335
I'm just here.

1126
01:46:15,849 --> 01:46:18,689
Sir, did you have
the same nightmare again?

1127
01:46:37,787 --> 01:46:41,287
It was the chairman of the hotel I work at
who brought the tiger from North Korea.

1128
01:46:41,374 --> 01:46:42,964
He received it
as a token of their friendship

1129
01:46:43,043 --> 01:46:44,383
during his visit a long time ago.

1130
01:46:45,420 --> 01:46:46,380
Is that so?

1131
01:46:48,840 --> 01:46:51,380
But you said
you were looking for the tiger.

1132
01:46:51,676 --> 01:46:53,346
Why did you come to eat red bean porridge?

1133
01:46:53,928 --> 01:46:55,558
Is this restaurant relevant to the tiger?

1134
01:46:55,639 --> 01:46:57,679
Red bean porridge is
the tiger's favorite food.

1135
01:46:58,308 --> 01:47:00,388
Isn't it only natural
that the porridge comes to mind

1136
01:47:00,477 --> 01:47:01,597
when I think about the tiger?

1137
01:47:05,023 --> 01:47:07,033
I don't get how that's natural.

1138
01:47:09,569 --> 01:47:11,569
You just wanted to have
red bean porridge, didn't you?

1139
01:47:11,655 --> 01:47:13,945
This restaurant was
on The Guys Who Died After Eating.

1140
01:47:14,199 --> 01:47:15,329
Kim Jun-hyun...

1141
01:47:15,408 --> 01:47:16,698
Him again.

1142
01:47:16,826 --> 01:47:19,786
He ate five balls of sticky rice cake
all at once.

1143
01:47:20,497 --> 01:47:23,167
That guy. He's not an ordinary man.

1144
01:47:24,709 --> 01:47:26,129
How many can you eat at once?

1145
01:47:26,586 --> 01:47:28,296
I told you I had to go to work.

1146
01:47:29,047 --> 01:47:31,007
I don't have time to eat this right now.

1147
01:47:31,091 --> 01:47:33,431
You must take your time
to eat this porridge.

1148
01:47:33,510 --> 01:47:36,430
If you eat this in a hurry,
the hot rice cakes will burn your mouth.

1149
01:47:36,805 --> 01:47:37,965
I gave you the money.

1150
01:47:38,056 --> 01:47:39,266
Since you accepted the money,

1151
01:47:39,808 --> 01:47:41,228
please fix my eyes.

1152
01:47:45,689 --> 01:47:46,819
A long time ago,

1153
01:47:47,482 --> 01:47:50,442
do you know why a rice cake seller
was eaten by a tiger?

1154
01:47:52,028 --> 01:47:54,738
The seller gave away the rice cake
too easily

1155
01:47:54,823 --> 01:47:57,083
when the tiger said
that it could save his life.

1156
01:47:57,617 --> 01:47:59,037
That's why he was eaten alive.

1157
01:47:59,369 --> 01:48:01,249
The seller should have negotiated first.

1158
01:48:05,083 --> 01:48:08,593
Then I would have to live
with the woman with sunglasses forever?

1159
01:48:08,670 --> 01:48:10,710
No, bring her to my hotel.

1160
01:48:10,797 --> 01:48:13,427
I can let her stay there for a few days
and send her to the afterlife.

1161
01:48:13,675 --> 01:48:16,795
Well, if she lived a good life,
she could go in a limousine.

1162
01:48:22,267 --> 01:48:24,267
THE SAMDO RIVER

1163
01:48:24,352 --> 01:48:26,192
THIS LIFE

1164
01:48:26,271 --> 01:48:28,481
THE AFTERLIFE

1165
01:48:48,585 --> 01:48:50,705
I heard that there will be
a new manager at the hotel.

1166
01:48:51,296 --> 01:48:52,126
Yes,

1167
01:48:52,505 --> 01:48:54,715
I will retire soon.

1168
01:48:55,508 --> 01:48:58,178
I plan to go on a lot of fishing trips.

1169
01:48:58,595 --> 01:48:59,635
You don't

1170
01:49:00,346 --> 01:49:02,466
have that much time left.

1171
01:49:04,726 --> 01:49:08,726
Does that mean
I don't have much time left in this world?

1172
01:49:15,195 --> 01:49:17,315
I should start
to get things in order then.

1173
01:49:25,079 --> 01:49:26,619
I won't work at your hotel.

1174
01:49:26,873 --> 01:49:29,963
I've been offered a job
from 3 of the top 100 hotels

1175
01:49:30,043 --> 01:49:32,003
listed on Forbes.

1176
01:49:32,378 --> 01:49:33,758
Hotel del Luna

1177
01:49:34,047 --> 01:49:37,757
doesn't need a manager
with the Harvard MBA like me.

1178
01:49:38,426 --> 01:49:39,586
You don't need an MBA.

1179
01:49:40,720 --> 01:49:42,260
You can see ghosts now.

1180
01:49:43,473 --> 01:49:44,683
You're perfect for my hotel.

1181
01:49:45,600 --> 01:49:46,890
And what was that? Forbes?

1182
01:49:47,018 --> 01:49:48,808
I'm sure they wanted to hire you

1183
01:49:48,895 --> 01:49:50,855
when they didn't know
you could see ghosts.

1184
01:49:51,147 --> 01:49:52,567
If you don't work at our hotel,

1185
01:49:52,649 --> 01:49:54,569
the only thing you can become is a shaman.

1186
01:49:56,236 --> 01:49:59,486
You could be a comedian if you know
how to eat the whole bread at once.

1187
01:50:01,241 --> 01:50:02,371
Will you perform an exorcism?

1188
01:50:02,450 --> 01:50:03,700
I can get used to it.

1189
01:50:03,785 --> 01:50:06,615
Once I get used to seeing ghosts,
I can get used to ignoring them.

1190
01:50:07,288 --> 01:50:08,118
Is that so?

1191
01:50:09,415 --> 01:50:11,245
Shall we check if you can...

1192
01:50:12,627 --> 01:50:13,457
ignore them?

1193
01:50:41,906 --> 01:50:43,156
Go get the coffee.

1194
01:50:43,616 --> 01:50:46,906
Just like you said,
if you can ignore all of them

1195
01:50:47,245 --> 01:50:49,405
and bring the coffee
without spilling a drop,

1196
01:50:50,331 --> 01:50:51,501
I will believe you.

1197
01:52:24,092 --> 01:52:26,392
You can barely bring a cup of coffee.

1198
01:52:27,011 --> 01:52:28,971
Do you think
those posh hotels will want you?

1199
01:52:38,481 --> 01:52:41,651
But when will the new manager
start working?

1200
01:52:41,901 --> 01:52:43,241
Once he starts here,

1201
01:52:43,403 --> 01:52:46,113
will you leave the hotel
right away, Mr. No?

1202
01:52:46,864 --> 01:52:48,494
He's been stuck here for a long time now.

1203
01:52:48,574 --> 01:52:50,164
Now, you'll get to live your life.

1204
01:52:50,326 --> 01:52:51,366
Come visit us sometimes

1205
01:52:51,452 --> 01:52:53,622
and tell us what's going on
in the realm of the living.

1206
01:52:54,122 --> 01:52:56,372
What good will that do for us,
the dead souls?

1207
01:52:57,166 --> 01:52:58,666
Have fun

1208
01:52:58,876 --> 01:53:01,666
and come back much later.

1209
01:53:02,672 --> 01:53:05,802
You should work on emptying
all your sorrows

1210
01:53:05,925 --> 01:53:09,295
and walk over to the afterlife
for a new beginning.

1211
01:53:11,889 --> 01:53:14,729
I hoped to send all of you off myself
during my time here,

1212
01:53:15,727 --> 01:53:17,267
but that was only wishful thinking.

1213
01:53:18,187 --> 01:53:21,897
Without you, who will help manage
her bad temper?

1214
01:53:22,316 --> 01:53:24,356
The new manager
doesn't seem trustworthy yet.

1215
01:53:24,444 --> 01:53:25,574
Where is everyone?

1216
01:53:34,662 --> 01:53:38,712
I was saying goodbye to everyone
since I'll be leaving soon.

1217
01:53:41,002 --> 01:53:43,762
Seon-bi, you passed the State Exam
when you were alive, right?

1218
01:53:43,838 --> 01:53:44,918
Yes, ma'am.

1219
01:53:45,298 --> 01:53:47,468
-Just so you know--
-Zip it.

1220
01:53:47,550 --> 01:53:50,720
Isn't that better
than the modern-day Harvard MBA?

1221
01:53:51,137 --> 01:53:53,427
The MBA doesn't even hold a candle to it.

1222
01:53:53,514 --> 01:53:54,394
Ms. Choe.

1223
01:53:54,474 --> 01:53:56,604
You said you lived in a mansion
that had 99 rooms, correct?

1224
01:53:56,684 --> 01:53:57,774
Yes, ma'am.

1225
01:53:58,144 --> 01:54:00,734
I had countless employees.

1226
01:54:00,813 --> 01:54:01,773
And you?

1227
01:54:01,856 --> 01:54:04,396
I was the richest
and attended the top school

1228
01:54:04,484 --> 01:54:05,744
in the whole Gyeongseong.

1229
01:54:05,818 --> 01:54:07,988
Right? Before you guys died,

1230
01:54:08,071 --> 01:54:10,661
you were way better off
than Koo Chan-sung.

1231
01:54:11,032 --> 01:54:14,622
He thinks he's something
because of that joke of a Forbes list.

1232
01:54:14,702 --> 01:54:15,702
Darn it!

1233
01:54:22,502 --> 01:54:25,172
Ms. Jang, just like last time,

1234
01:54:25,254 --> 01:54:29,054
I'm afraid I'll have to
check into the hospital for a few days.

1235
01:54:30,384 --> 01:54:31,514
Are you not feeling well?

1236
01:54:31,594 --> 01:54:35,314
When will that Koo Chan-sung be here?

1237
01:54:35,389 --> 01:54:37,309
He claimed he could endure it,
so I let him.

1238
01:54:37,517 --> 01:54:39,057
He'll crack in a few days though.

1239
01:54:40,144 --> 01:54:41,944
He's just too weak, you see.

1240
01:54:43,231 --> 01:54:45,861
Now that there's another living human
to take your spot,

1241
01:54:45,942 --> 01:54:47,402
I'll let you as I agreed.

1242
01:54:47,568 --> 01:54:51,068
Enjoy your last moments
as a living human being

1243
01:54:52,281 --> 01:54:53,321
and move on.

1244
01:55:08,297 --> 01:55:10,467
He's been serving her for decades.

1245
01:55:10,633 --> 01:55:13,433
Would it have killed her
to seem more concerned?

1246
01:55:28,985 --> 01:55:30,815
I look forward to working with you.

1247
01:55:31,154 --> 01:55:32,414
Nice to meet you.

1248
01:55:37,160 --> 01:55:39,500
THE FOUR SEASONS OF BAEKDU MOUNTAIN

1249
01:55:43,082 --> 01:55:44,962
SIBERIAN TIGER IN BAEKDU MOUNTAIN

1250
01:56:18,784 --> 01:56:21,584
Stay calm. You just have to ignore it.

1251
01:56:39,805 --> 01:56:40,635
Mr. Koo!

1252
01:56:44,310 --> 01:56:45,140
That's right.

1253
01:56:45,561 --> 01:56:48,271
My clients are VIPs from abroad,

1254
01:56:48,773 --> 01:56:49,903
not ghosts.

1255
01:57:14,340 --> 01:57:15,260
Mr. Koo?

1256
01:57:18,177 --> 01:57:19,387
Don't make a sound.

1257
01:57:19,804 --> 01:57:23,104
If I keep quiet, she'll leave me alone
just like before.

1258
01:57:24,600 --> 01:57:25,690
Please come and say hello.

1259
01:57:28,396 --> 01:57:30,936
What do I do? I already looked at them,

1260
01:57:31,023 --> 01:57:32,483
so I can't simply turn around.

1261
01:57:32,817 --> 01:57:33,777
But if I make a sound,

1262
01:57:33,859 --> 01:57:36,069
this ghost will take her shades off
and come at me.

1263
01:57:38,030 --> 01:57:39,370
Mr. Koo?

1264
01:57:40,074 --> 01:57:42,664
How can I not answer my boss, though?

1265
01:57:43,452 --> 01:57:46,542
But I don't think I can ignore the ghost
if she takes off her sunglasses.

1266
01:57:48,416 --> 01:57:49,416
So...

1267
01:57:50,584 --> 01:57:51,594
I'll...

1268
01:58:18,279 --> 01:58:19,319
What was that?

1269
01:58:20,948 --> 01:58:22,368
I thought you were going to ignore it?

1270
01:58:22,867 --> 01:58:24,407
Instead, you splashed into the water.

1271
01:58:26,746 --> 01:58:28,156
What about the next time?

1272
01:58:28,956 --> 01:58:30,826
Will you jump off the roof?

1273
01:58:34,628 --> 01:58:37,088
If I do, I'll be going
to your hotel as a guest.

1274
01:58:37,465 --> 01:58:38,795
I won't go there again before then.

1275
01:58:39,300 --> 01:58:41,050
I'll ignore whatever I see.

1276
01:58:43,721 --> 01:58:44,851
What's this?

1277
01:58:46,807 --> 01:58:48,807
I guess you couldn't ignore this.

1278
01:58:49,894 --> 01:58:51,064
You're curious

1279
01:58:51,604 --> 01:58:54,234
about what happened
to this last Siberian tiger.

1280
01:58:56,400 --> 01:58:57,490
What happened to him?

1281
01:59:01,238 --> 01:59:02,358
Let's go find out.

1282
01:59:18,297 --> 01:59:19,217
Ring the bell.

1283
01:59:21,467 --> 01:59:22,927
This makes no sense.

1284
01:59:23,135 --> 01:59:24,755
He is the chairman
of the hotel I work for.

1285
01:59:24,845 --> 01:59:27,465
A mere employee can't just pay
a visit to his chairman's house.

1286
01:59:27,556 --> 01:59:28,426
Why not?

1287
01:59:28,891 --> 01:59:31,771
You said yourself
that you were scouted, right?

1288
01:59:33,562 --> 01:59:34,862
Where's your pride?

1289
01:59:35,773 --> 01:59:39,693
Let me call his secretary
and receive permission to-- Hey!

1290
01:59:45,574 --> 01:59:49,164
It's the first time an employee
has come to see me in my sickbed.

1291
01:59:49,245 --> 01:59:50,695
I heard you were ill, sir.

1292
01:59:50,788 --> 01:59:53,828
I wanted to show my respect.
But I apologize for visiting so abruptly.

1293
01:59:53,916 --> 01:59:55,286
No need to apologize.

1294
01:59:56,085 --> 01:59:57,835
Anyway, is she your wife?

1295
02:00:01,841 --> 02:00:04,971
Yes, she wanted to show her respect too.

1296
02:00:05,678 --> 02:00:07,508
Well, you seem to be a couple in love.

1297
02:00:08,264 --> 02:00:12,064
I've stayed only in my room
ever since I fell sick.

1298
02:00:12,560 --> 02:00:15,940
There was no one to talk to either,
so this is fun.

1299
02:00:28,617 --> 02:00:30,697
She must be looking for the bathroom.

1300
02:00:32,204 --> 02:00:33,874
Hey, this looks expensive.

1301
02:00:34,957 --> 02:00:36,077
Is it authentic? Tell me.

1302
02:00:41,172 --> 02:00:43,722
She lived abroad for so long

1303
02:00:43,841 --> 02:00:45,591
that she speaks casually with everyone.

1304
02:00:46,093 --> 02:00:48,143
Is that so?

1305
02:00:54,685 --> 02:00:56,225
You should sit back down.

1306
02:01:00,816 --> 02:01:02,856
You must have an eye for paintings.

1307
02:01:03,903 --> 02:01:05,073
This is a painting

1308
02:01:05,487 --> 02:01:08,697
by a famous North Korean artist.

1309
02:01:08,782 --> 02:01:11,702
When I visited the North,
they gave it to me as a gift

1310
02:01:12,119 --> 02:01:13,869
along with a Siberian tiger.

1311
02:01:13,954 --> 02:01:16,424
We saw the tiger on display, sir.

1312
02:01:17,333 --> 02:01:19,083
So that tiger...

1313
02:01:21,754 --> 02:01:25,424
I brought him here from North Korea,

1314
02:01:26,133 --> 02:01:29,263
but he didn't mate while he lived here

1315
02:01:29,762 --> 02:01:32,432
and ended up dying as a lonesome soul.

1316
02:01:33,349 --> 02:01:36,439
Because there's no need for him
to leave anything meaningful here.

1317
02:01:38,395 --> 02:01:40,515
Everything that is precious to him

1318
02:01:41,357 --> 02:01:43,687
lies in a place he can't go back to.

1319
02:01:45,402 --> 02:01:47,782
That's why I feel sorry for him.

1320
02:01:48,113 --> 02:01:51,283
I keep seeing the tiger in my dreams.

1321
02:01:53,160 --> 02:01:55,370
The one who brought him here,
should return him.

1322
02:01:55,788 --> 02:01:57,998
But the stuffed tiger has
already become a symbol

1323
02:01:58,082 --> 02:01:59,792
of exchanges between the two Koreas.

1324
02:02:00,459 --> 02:02:02,839
It's not up to me to get rid of it

1325
02:02:03,462 --> 02:02:05,172
or send it back.

1326
02:02:53,971 --> 02:02:56,561
I guess this photo will be the only proof

1327
02:02:58,517 --> 02:03:01,767
of the time I've spent
working at this hotel.

1328
02:03:03,605 --> 02:03:06,565
Will she remember
a mere human being like me

1329
02:03:07,151 --> 02:03:08,991
who's just passing by here?

1330
02:03:33,427 --> 02:03:35,507
The tiger was definitely
next to the chairman.

1331
02:03:36,180 --> 02:03:38,060
Why did you let it get away
instead of catching it?

1332
02:03:38,140 --> 02:03:40,350
It didn't want to come with me.
I can't force it.

1333
02:03:40,517 --> 02:03:43,847
It looks like it's waiting
until the chairman dies.

1334
02:03:44,104 --> 02:03:46,154
Is the tiger making the chairman ill?

1335
02:03:47,191 --> 02:03:48,731
If that's the case, it's really dangerous.

1336
02:03:48,817 --> 02:03:50,397
We don't have time to eat hoe right now.

1337
02:03:50,486 --> 02:03:53,526
I looked at Baekdu Mountain earlier,
so I suddenly craved hoe.

1338
02:03:54,406 --> 02:03:56,736
You looked at a mountain.
Why are you craving fish?

1339
02:03:58,535 --> 02:04:00,825
The anthem goes,
"Baekdu Mountain and East Sea."

1340
02:04:00,913 --> 02:04:02,213
They come as a set.

1341
02:04:02,623 --> 02:04:06,173
It's only natural to crave seafood
when you see Baekdu Mountain.

1342
02:04:06,251 --> 02:04:08,501
You just wanted to have hoe.

1343
02:04:10,297 --> 02:04:11,417
I don't care what it is.

1344
02:04:11,507 --> 02:04:13,927
A ghost is torturing a human.
We must go back.

1345
02:04:14,301 --> 02:04:15,221
Sure.

1346
02:04:16,387 --> 02:04:18,177
You do have to go back there.

1347
02:04:18,263 --> 02:04:21,353
Go and tell the chairman
that you can get rid of the tiger

1348
02:04:22,810 --> 02:04:23,980
in return for something.

1349
02:04:25,896 --> 02:04:26,936
In return for what?

1350
02:04:27,022 --> 02:04:29,152
The expensive painting we saw earlier.

1351
02:04:29,942 --> 02:04:30,982
In return for that.

1352
02:04:31,652 --> 02:04:32,532
What?

1353
02:04:32,611 --> 02:04:35,071
He'll give it to you if you tell him
he's sick because of the tiger.

1354
02:04:35,155 --> 02:04:38,525
That old geezer is loaded.

1355
02:04:41,286 --> 02:04:43,576
Now, I understand
how you make profits with your hotel.

1356
02:04:44,415 --> 02:04:47,535
You extort money from people
who are suffering because of ghosts.

1357
02:04:47,626 --> 02:04:49,876
Is it in my job descriptions
as a human manager?

1358
02:04:49,962 --> 02:04:50,962
That's right.

1359
02:04:51,839 --> 02:04:53,839
It will be your job from now on.

1360
02:04:56,468 --> 02:04:58,598
I won't scam people like that.

1361
02:05:07,729 --> 02:05:09,609
Is this how you conned my dad too?

1362
02:05:13,235 --> 02:05:15,525
I saved your dad's life.

1363
02:05:16,155 --> 02:05:17,985
And in exchange, I got you.

1364
02:05:18,198 --> 02:05:21,028
That's why I'm protecting you too.

1365
02:05:21,827 --> 02:05:23,537
Without me by your side,

1366
02:05:24,788 --> 02:05:25,868
you'll be dead.

1367
02:05:26,748 --> 02:05:28,418
The vengeful ghost will torture me?

1368
02:05:29,918 --> 02:05:32,418
I think you've done that enough yourself.

1369
02:05:40,637 --> 02:05:42,557
I've made good on my promise to you.

1370
02:05:44,808 --> 02:05:47,018
I'm going back to my human life.

1371
02:06:15,714 --> 02:06:17,634
Take off your sunglasses
if that's what you want.

1372
02:06:17,716 --> 02:06:20,006
I even saw a tiger.
Nothing can scare me now!

1373
02:06:20,302 --> 02:06:21,472
I'm not scared of you now.

1374
02:06:21,553 --> 02:06:22,473
Take them off!

1375
02:06:48,330 --> 02:06:50,790
I've been waiting and wondering
when you'd come.

1376
02:06:51,708 --> 02:06:53,418
You said you've worked there for 30 years.

1377
02:06:53,752 --> 02:06:56,672
Did that woman force you to work there
for 30 years?

1378
02:06:56,755 --> 02:06:57,755
No.

1379
02:06:58,924 --> 02:07:01,394
It was my decision to work at the hotel.

1380
02:07:01,802 --> 02:07:04,222
You spent half of your life
working at a place like that?

1381
02:07:04,304 --> 02:07:08,934
Because Hotel del Luna was worth my time.

1382
02:07:09,685 --> 02:07:11,845
I don't understand its worth.

1383
02:07:12,854 --> 02:07:14,274
I don't want to extort

1384
02:07:14,356 --> 02:07:16,936
billions of won from the chairman
under her instruction.

1385
02:07:18,318 --> 02:07:19,528
And I don't think I can either.

1386
02:07:19,611 --> 02:07:20,781
Hotel del Luna

1387
02:07:20,988 --> 02:07:24,948
can't be explained by the logic
of the human world.

1388
02:07:25,075 --> 02:07:28,865
The value of money and power
seems different at the hotel.

1389
02:07:29,913 --> 02:07:32,753
That's why I can't possibly judge

1390
02:07:32,833 --> 02:07:35,963
what Ms. Jang does for the hotel
by our human standards.

1391
02:07:38,964 --> 02:07:40,974
I'm sure you hate the hotel

1392
02:07:41,883 --> 02:07:44,053
and don't want to face it right now.

1393
02:07:44,678 --> 02:07:46,258
I'm sure you want to avoid it.

1394
02:07:47,180 --> 02:07:51,060
However, if you gather
your courage and face it,

1395
02:07:51,602 --> 02:07:54,862
you might be able to find

1396
02:07:55,314 --> 02:07:57,904
the worth of the hotel, just like I did.

1397
02:08:01,153 --> 02:08:02,153
Chan-sung.

1398
02:08:03,655 --> 02:08:04,945
What are you doing there alone?

1399
02:08:05,866 --> 02:08:07,116
I'm having a conversation.

1400
02:08:07,784 --> 02:08:08,874
By yourself?

1401
02:08:22,215 --> 02:08:23,795
He must be lonely.

1402
02:08:33,560 --> 02:08:36,480
Through your job, you'll find out

1403
02:08:37,689 --> 02:08:40,979
a secret world that
no one else knows about.

1404
02:08:42,944 --> 02:08:44,994
Don't you think it will be fun?

1405
02:09:18,772 --> 02:09:19,772
Oh!

1406
02:09:26,405 --> 02:09:27,775
Mr. No.

1407
02:09:35,872 --> 02:09:36,872
Ms. Jang.

1408
02:09:37,666 --> 02:09:40,086
Mr. No is here as a guest.

1409
02:09:55,934 --> 02:09:56,984
Ms. Jang.

1410
02:09:58,311 --> 02:10:00,111
I worked here every day,

1411
02:10:00,564 --> 02:10:02,614
but it feels weird
to come here as a guest.

1412
02:10:03,525 --> 02:10:04,565
Are you dead?

1413
02:10:05,861 --> 02:10:07,071
I'm sorry.

1414
02:10:07,154 --> 02:10:10,744
I lost my life while I was out.

1415
02:10:13,201 --> 02:10:14,951
I finally let you go.

1416
02:10:15,746 --> 02:10:18,036
You probably didn't have
a chance to live like a human being.

1417
02:10:18,206 --> 02:10:20,416
As I served my guests here,

1418
02:10:20,917 --> 02:10:24,667
I lived a meaningful life in my own way.

1419
02:10:26,423 --> 02:10:30,053
A long time ago,
when I wanted to end my life...

1420
02:10:31,011 --> 02:10:33,011
If I hadn't met you that day,

1421
02:10:33,722 --> 02:10:37,772
my life would have been
short and pitiable.

1422
02:10:39,102 --> 02:10:40,852
I'm really glad

1423
02:10:40,937 --> 02:10:44,357
that I could stay at Hotel del Luna.

1424
02:10:44,941 --> 02:10:46,231
Glad, my foot.

1425
02:10:47,069 --> 02:10:50,199
You couldn't even make a family
who would remember you.

1426
02:10:50,572 --> 02:10:53,372
As I was the only one
who got older at this hotel,

1427
02:10:54,451 --> 02:10:58,161
you were my sister,

1428
02:11:00,290 --> 02:11:01,920
my daughter,

1429
02:11:03,668 --> 02:11:05,418
and my granddaughter.

1430
02:11:09,216 --> 02:11:11,466
Now that you have a reliable replacement,

1431
02:11:12,302 --> 02:11:14,182
I can leave without worries.

1432
02:11:27,359 --> 02:11:28,359
Since...

1433
02:11:30,153 --> 02:11:31,573
I can't die,

1434
02:11:33,240 --> 02:11:35,660
I can't tell you
that we'll meet again someday...

1435
02:11:36,827 --> 02:11:37,907
or something like that.

1436
02:11:48,672 --> 02:11:49,882
I hope

1437
02:11:50,841 --> 02:11:54,091
that your time will start running
once again someday.

1438
02:13:21,181 --> 02:13:24,141
I apologize for coming back
so late at night.

1439
02:13:24,684 --> 02:13:26,444
I needed to say something important.

1440
02:13:27,270 --> 02:13:28,980
Is it about the tiger?

1441
02:13:29,898 --> 02:13:31,898
The woman you were with earlier.

1442
02:13:31,983 --> 02:13:34,443
Ms. Jang Man-wol came by to see me.

1443
02:13:34,903 --> 02:13:36,113
Did she tell you

1444
02:13:36,821 --> 02:13:38,661
that the tiger was wandering around you?

1445
02:13:40,992 --> 02:13:45,002
I brought him here,
and he could never go back home.

1446
02:13:45,914 --> 02:13:49,044
I've always been sorry for him because
it felt like I was keeping his soul here

1447
02:13:49,584 --> 02:13:51,004
even after his life ended.

1448
02:13:54,631 --> 02:13:55,631
Come out.

1449
02:13:56,049 --> 02:13:58,929
Stop staying in that body
as if you were still alive.

1450
02:14:00,053 --> 02:14:01,053
Come out.

1451
02:14:01,680 --> 02:14:03,060
I'll help you leave.

1452
02:14:05,558 --> 02:14:07,848
As a punishment
for bringing over the tiger,

1453
02:14:08,103 --> 02:14:10,403
she said she had to take my painting.

1454
02:14:11,982 --> 02:14:13,402
I know it's hard to believe,

1455
02:14:14,109 --> 02:14:15,859
but the tiger wasn't just your dream.

1456
02:14:17,404 --> 02:14:19,204
I gave the painting to her.

1457
02:14:21,366 --> 02:14:24,236
If I could atone for what I did,

1458
02:14:24,786 --> 02:14:26,826
I could give up even more than that.

1459
02:14:31,251 --> 02:14:33,341
The painting was of Baekdu Mountain.

1460
02:14:33,795 --> 02:14:35,205
The mountain and the tiger

1461
02:14:36,089 --> 02:14:37,419
are part of a set.

1462
02:14:38,675 --> 02:14:41,085
I wonder why I never thought of that.

1463
02:15:02,198 --> 02:15:03,948
The place you wish to go to

1464
02:15:05,160 --> 02:15:07,620
no longer exists in this world.

1465
02:15:08,371 --> 02:15:11,621
However, the man who brought you here
provided a place for you to stay.

1466
02:15:13,293 --> 02:15:14,293
Go...

1467
02:15:15,670 --> 02:15:16,920
and rest in peace.

1468
02:17:17,417 --> 02:17:18,417
Excuse me.

1469
02:17:21,588 --> 02:17:24,798
I know where you should go.

1470
02:17:29,220 --> 02:17:30,430
I'll take you there.

1471
02:17:42,817 --> 02:17:45,857
I always avoided you
because I hated having you on my tail.

1472
02:17:46,738 --> 02:17:49,158
Come to think of it, I never asked you
why you were following me.

1473
02:17:54,329 --> 02:17:55,709
I thought about it.

1474
02:17:55,914 --> 02:17:59,424
I know you couldn't see when you were
alive, but maybe you can now.

1475
02:17:59,626 --> 02:18:01,536
Stop thinking that you can't,

1476
02:18:02,003 --> 02:18:03,213
and take another look.

1477
02:18:20,396 --> 02:18:21,516
See?

1478
02:18:22,148 --> 02:18:23,318
Your eyes are back.

1479
02:19:17,620 --> 02:19:19,660
THE FOUR SEASONS OF BAEKDU MOUNTAIN

1480
02:19:20,623 --> 02:19:23,843
Because there's no need for him
to leave anything meaningful here.

1481
02:19:24,419 --> 02:19:26,549
Everything that is precious to him

1482
02:19:27,338 --> 02:19:29,718
lies in a place he can't go back to.

1483
02:19:38,349 --> 02:19:40,349
Did the tiger return safely
to Baekdu Mountain?

1484
02:19:41,936 --> 02:19:43,476
I'm sorry I was mistaken about you.

1485
02:19:50,903 --> 02:19:51,743
That's right.

1486
02:19:51,821 --> 02:19:54,321
The chairman said a burden on your heart
is what makes you sick.

1487
02:19:54,407 --> 02:19:56,487
I'M SORRY I WAS MISTAKEN ABOUT YOU

1488
02:19:56,576 --> 02:19:58,196
SENT

1489
02:19:58,328 --> 02:20:00,408
There. It's a decent thing to do.

1490
02:20:04,626 --> 02:20:05,536
Please don't.

1491
02:20:08,046 --> 02:20:10,206
-You shouldn't touch things like this.
-My goodness.

1492
02:20:10,298 --> 02:20:11,418
I'm so sorry.

1493
02:20:34,906 --> 02:20:36,196
Just ignore it.

1494
02:20:37,158 --> 02:20:38,238
You can do this.

1495
02:21:05,311 --> 02:21:07,441
FROM KOO CHAN-SUNG

1496
02:21:11,109 --> 02:21:12,779
She's not replying.

1497
02:21:38,970 --> 02:21:39,970
Excuse me?

1498
02:21:42,515 --> 02:21:44,805
Is the pool still open?

1499
02:21:46,644 --> 02:21:49,734
Yes, ma'am. It's open
even during the nights these days.

1500
02:21:50,523 --> 02:21:51,523
It's this way...

1501
02:21:52,608 --> 02:21:54,568
Got it. Thank you.

1502
02:22:09,333 --> 02:22:11,343
If you get attacked by those
who hold deep grudges,

1503
02:22:11,419 --> 02:22:12,799
you could end up getting killed.

1504
02:22:13,421 --> 02:22:15,131
You should learn to differentiate them.

1505
02:24:10,039 --> 02:24:12,419
The tiger has returned safely
to Baekdu Mountain,

1506
02:24:14,752 --> 02:24:17,002
and I'm here to forgive you in person.

1507
02:24:20,091 --> 02:24:21,381
Thank you.

1508
02:24:41,320 --> 02:24:42,950
I envy trees.

1509
02:24:43,864 --> 02:24:45,534
They don't have to wander around.

1510
02:24:45,991 --> 02:24:48,161
It must be nice to just put down roots
and settle down.

1511
02:24:50,246 --> 02:24:51,076
What?

1512
02:24:51,288 --> 02:24:53,168
You'll build a house for me
with this tree?

1513
02:24:54,458 --> 02:24:55,538
Forget it.

1514
02:24:55,751 --> 02:24:57,801
I don't plan on building a house
and living with you.

1515
02:25:24,405 --> 02:25:25,525
You woke up.

1516
02:25:25,906 --> 02:25:27,906
Ms. Jang is waiting for you, Mr. Manager.

1517
02:25:27,992 --> 02:25:29,412
I told you I'm not the manager...

1518
02:25:36,709 --> 02:25:38,499
It's your first time here at night, right?

1519
02:26:38,395 --> 02:26:41,355
This is what Hotel del Luna
really looks like.

1520
02:26:47,238 --> 02:26:49,778
Through your job, you'll find out

1521
02:26:49,990 --> 02:26:52,580
a secret world that
no one else knows about.

1522
02:26:53,285 --> 02:26:55,445
Don't you think it will be fun?

1523
02:27:05,548 --> 02:27:06,588
Ms. Jang is here.

1524
02:28:19,747 --> 02:28:22,497
This is what it was like
to have a warm body

1525
02:28:22,708 --> 02:28:23,708
with a beating heart.

1526
02:28:23,792 --> 02:28:25,842
Did you cast a spell on me or something?

1527
02:28:26,253 --> 02:28:28,013
Is that why I dreamed about you?

1528
02:28:28,339 --> 02:28:31,429
Koo Chan-sung. I thought you were weak,

1529
02:28:31,717 --> 02:28:33,337
but you're actually very healthy.

1530
02:28:33,427 --> 02:28:36,347
Do you know what Ms. Jang was like
when she was alive?

1531
02:28:36,430 --> 02:28:37,640
Leaves have sprouted.

1532
02:28:37,723 --> 02:28:40,353
Your time will start flowing again.

1533
02:28:40,434 --> 02:28:41,984
Let's get Mr. Koo out of the hotel.

1534
02:28:42,561 --> 02:28:45,151
If he goes crazy
and roams around like a madman,

1535
02:28:45,230 --> 02:28:47,610
he won't be able to come here
even though he sees ghosts.

1536
02:28:51,320 --> 02:28:53,570
Subtitle translation by Wayne Ryu
